{"mode":"editor","version":1,"windowDimensions":{"x":254,"y":23,"width":1024,"height":752,"maximized":false},"grammars":{"deserializer":"GrammarRegistry","grammarOverridesByPath":{}},"project":{"paths":["/Users/joegesualdo/Downloads/the-shawshank-redemption-english-yify-36147"],"buffers":[{"load":true,"text":"﻿1\r\n00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:27,086\r\n[THE INKSPOTS' \"IF I DIDN'T CARE\"\r\nPLAYING ON RADIO]\r\n\r\n2\r\n00:02:05,542 --> 00:02:07,501\r\nMAN:\r\nMr. Dufresne, describe...\r\n\r\n3\r\n00:02:07,710 --> 00:02:12,047\r\n...the confrontation you had with\r\nyour wife the night she was murdered.\r\n\r\n4\r\n00:02:16,719 --> 00:02:18,387\r\nIt was very bitter.\r\n\r\n5\r\n00:02:18,721 --> 00:02:23,058\r\nShe said she was glad I knew,\r\nthat she hated all the sneaking around.\r\n\r\n6\r\n00:02:24,561 --> 00:02:28,063\r\nAnd she said that she wanted\r\na divorce in Reno.\r\n\r\n7\r\n00:02:28,314 --> 00:02:31,984\r\n- What was your response?\r\n- I told her I would not grant one.\r\n\r\n8\r\n00:02:32,193 --> 00:02:35,362\r\n\"I'll see you in hell\r\nbefore I see you in Reno.\"\r\n\r\n9\r\n00:02:35,572 --> 00:02:38,907\r\nThose were your words,\r\naccording to your neighbors.\r\n\r\n10\r\n00:02:39,951 --> 00:02:41,577\r\nIf they say so.\r\n\r\n11\r\n00:02:42,078 --> 00:02:44,621\r\nI really don't remember. I was upset.\r\n\r\n12\r\n00:02:44,914 --> 00:02:47,332\r\nWhat happened after you argued\r\nwith your wife?\r\n\r\n13\r\n00:02:48,501 --> 00:02:50,252\r\nShe packed a bag.\r\n\r\n14\r\n00:02:51,421 --> 00:02:54,590\r\nShe packed a bag to go\r\nand stay with Mr. Quentin.\r\n\r\n15\r\n00:02:55,258 --> 00:02:59,344\r\nD. A: Glenn Quentin, golf pro\r\nat the Snowden Hills Country Club...\r\n\r\n16\r\n00:02:59,554 --> 00:03:02,681\r\n...whom you had discovered\r\nwas your wife's lover.\r\n\r\n17\r\n00:03:04,976 --> 00:03:06,185\r\nDid you follow her?\r\n\r\n18\r\n00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:09,605\r\nI went to a few bars first.\r\n\r\n19\r\n00:03:09,814 --> 00:03:14,193\r\nLater, I drove to his house\r\nto confront them. They weren't home.\r\n\r\n20\r\n00:03:14,777 --> 00:03:16,278\r\nI parked in the turnout...\r\n\r\n21\r\n00:03:16,988 --> 00:03:17,988\r\n...and waited.\r\n\r\n22\r\n00:03:18,198 --> 00:03:19,865\r\nD. A:\r\nWith what intention?\r\n\r\n23\r\n00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:21,909\r\nANDY:\r\nI'm not sure.\r\n\r\n24\r\n00:03:23,036 --> 00:03:24,494\r\nI was confused...\r\n\r\n25\r\n00:03:24,704 --> 00:03:25,954\r\n...drunk.\r\n\r\n26\r\n00:03:27,290 --> 00:03:28,582\r\nI think...\r\n\r\n27\r\n00:03:28,791 --> 00:03:30,959\r\n...mostly I wanted to scare them.\r\n\r\n28\r\n00:03:31,127 --> 00:03:34,504\r\nWhen they arrived, you went up\r\nto the house and murdered them.\r\n\r\n29\r\n00:03:34,672 --> 00:03:36,798\r\nANDY:\r\nNo, I was sobering up.\r\n\r\n30\r\n00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:40,677\r\nI got back in the car\r\nand I drove home to sleep it off.\r\n\r\n31\r\n00:03:40,887 --> 00:03:43,847\r\nAlong the way, I threw my gun\r\ninto the Royal River.\r\n\r\n32\r\n00:03:44,057 --> 00:03:46,141\r\nI've been very clear on this point.\r\n\r\n33\r\n00:03:46,309 --> 00:03:50,354\r\nI get hazy where the cleaning woman\r\nshows up the following morning...\r\n\r\n34\r\n00:03:50,563 --> 00:03:53,148\r\n...and finds your wife in bed\r\nwith her lover...\r\n\r\n35\r\n00:03:53,358 --> 00:03:55,484\r\n...riddled with.38-caliber bullets.\r\n\r\n36\r\n00:03:56,819 --> 00:04:01,031\r\nDoes that strike you as a\r\nfantastic coincidence, or is it just me?\r\n\r\n37\r\n00:04:01,950 --> 00:04:02,950\r\nYes, it does.\r\n\r\n38\r\n00:04:03,159 --> 00:04:06,328\r\nYet you still maintain\r\nyou threw your gun into the river...\r\n\r\n39\r\n00:04:06,496 --> 00:04:08,580\r\n...before the murders took place.\r\n\r\n40\r\n00:04:08,790 --> 00:04:10,999\r\nThat's very convenient.\r\n\r\n41\r\n00:04:11,209 --> 00:04:12,876\r\nIt's the truth.\r\n\r\n42\r\n00:04:13,253 --> 00:04:17,839\r\nD. A: The police dragged that river for\r\nthree days, and nary a gun was found...\r\n\r\n43\r\n00:04:18,007 --> 00:04:22,135\r\n...so no comparison could be made\r\nbetween your gun and the bullets...\r\n\r\n44\r\n00:04:22,345 --> 00:04:25,764\r\n...taken from the bloodstained corpses\r\nof the victims.\r\n\r\n45\r\n00:04:26,432 --> 00:04:28,850\r\nAnd that also...\r\n\r\n46\r\n00:04:29,310 --> 00:04:32,729\r\n...is very convenient.\r\nIsn't it, Mr. Dufresne?\r\n\r\n47\r\n00:04:34,065 --> 00:04:36,149\r\nSince I am innocent of this crime...\r\n\r\n48\r\n00:04:36,359 --> 00:04:41,029\r\n...I find it decidedly inconvenient\r\nthat the gun was never found.\r\n\r\n49\r\n00:04:41,614 --> 00:04:43,615\r\n[THE INKSPOTS' \"IF I DIDN'T CARE\"\r\nPLAYING ON RADIO]\r\n\r\n50\r\n00:04:58,881 --> 00:05:02,217\r\nD. A: Ladies and gentlemen,\r\nyou've heard all the evidence.\r\n\r\n51\r\n00:05:02,427 --> 00:05:06,263\r\nWe have the accused at the scene\r\nof the crime. We have footprints.\r\n\r\n52\r\n00:05:06,472 --> 00:05:09,349\r\nBullets on the ground\r\nbearing his fingerprints.\r\n\r\n53\r\n00:05:09,559 --> 00:05:12,519\r\nA broken bourbon bottle,\r\nlikewise with fingerprints.\r\n\r\n54\r\n00:05:12,729 --> 00:05:14,271\r\nAnd most of all...\r\n\r\n55\r\n00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:17,566\r\n...we have a beautiful young woman\r\nand her lover...\r\n\r\n56\r\n00:05:17,734 --> 00:05:19,776\r\n...lying dead in each other's arms.\r\n\r\n57\r\n00:05:20,945 --> 00:05:23,572\r\nThey had sinned.\r\n\r\n58\r\n00:05:24,782 --> 00:05:27,326\r\nBut was their crime so great...\r\n\r\n59\r\n00:05:27,577 --> 00:05:29,786\r\n...as to merit a death sentence?\r\n\r\n60\r\n00:05:29,996 --> 00:05:32,289\r\nWhile you think about that...\r\n\r\n61\r\n00:05:33,750 --> 00:05:35,542\r\n...think about this:\r\n\r\n62\r\n00:05:36,419 --> 00:05:40,130\r\nA revolver holds six bullets, not eight.\r\n\r\n63\r\n00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:44,051\r\nI submit that this was not\r\na hot-blooded crime of passion.\r\n\r\n64\r\n00:05:44,260 --> 00:05:47,054\r\nThat at least could be understood,\r\nif not condoned.\r\n\r\n65\r\n00:05:47,263 --> 00:05:48,263\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n66\r\n00:05:48,473 --> 00:05:50,432\r\nThis was revenge...\r\n\r\n67\r\n00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:54,269\r\n...of a much more brutal,\r\ncold-blooded nature. Consider this:\r\n\r\n68\r\n00:05:54,437 --> 00:05:56,855\r\nFour bullets per victim.\r\n\r\n69\r\n00:05:57,607 --> 00:05:59,316\r\nNot six shots fired, but eight.\r\n\r\n70\r\n00:05:59,817 --> 00:06:03,445\r\nThat means that he fired\r\nthe gun empty...\r\n\r\n71\r\n00:06:03,654 --> 00:06:06,448\r\n...and then stopped to reload...\r\n\r\n72\r\n00:06:06,616 --> 00:06:09,284\r\n...so that he could shoot\r\neach of them again.\r\n\r\n73\r\n00:06:09,494 --> 00:06:12,079\r\nAn extra bullet per lover...\r\n\r\n74\r\n00:06:12,830 --> 00:06:14,623\r\n...right in the head.\r\n\r\n75\r\n00:06:18,127 --> 00:06:22,923\r\nYou strike me as a particularly icy\r\nand remorseless man, Mr. Dufresne.\r\n\r\n76\r\n00:06:23,299 --> 00:06:25,467\r\nIt chills my blood just to look at you.\r\n\r\n77\r\n00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:30,138\r\nBy the power vested in me\r\nby the state of Maine...\r\n\r\n78\r\n00:06:30,348 --> 00:06:34,643\r\n...I hereby order you to serve\r\ntwo life sentences back-to-back...\r\n\r\n79\r\n00:06:34,977 --> 00:06:37,521\r\n...one for each of your victims. So be it!\r\n\r\n80\r\n00:07:02,672 --> 00:07:03,839\r\nMAN:\r\nSit.\r\n\r\n81\r\n00:07:08,344 --> 00:07:11,179\r\nWe see you've served\r\n20 years of a life sentence?\r\n\r\n82\r\n00:07:12,140 --> 00:07:15,350\r\n- Yes, sir.\r\n- You feel you've been rehabilitated?\r\n\r\n83\r\n00:07:15,726 --> 00:07:18,353\r\nOh, yes, sir. Absolutely, sir.\r\n\r\n84\r\n00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:21,481\r\nI mean, I learned my lesson.\r\n\r\n85\r\n00:07:22,525 --> 00:07:25,986\r\nI can honestly say\r\nthat I'm a changed man.\r\n\r\n86\r\n00:07:29,198 --> 00:07:31,575\r\nI'm no longer a danger to society.\r\n\r\n87\r\n00:07:31,784 --> 00:07:33,743\r\nThat's God's honest truth.\r\n\r\n88\r\n00:08:07,904 --> 00:08:09,863\r\n[MEN CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]\r\n\r\n89\r\n00:08:10,072 --> 00:08:12,866\r\nFLOYD:\r\nHey, Red. How'd it go?\r\n\r\n90\r\n00:08:13,075 --> 00:08:15,243\r\nSame old shit, different day.\r\n\r\n91\r\n00:08:15,495 --> 00:08:17,370\r\nFLOYD:\r\nYeah, I know how you feel.\r\n\r\n92\r\n00:08:17,580 --> 00:08:19,581\r\nI'm up for rejection next week.\r\n\r\n93\r\n00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:22,876\r\nSNOOZE:\r\nYeah, I got rejected last week.\r\n\r\n94\r\n00:08:23,085 --> 00:08:24,377\r\nFLOYD:\r\nIt happens.\r\n\r\n95\r\n00:08:24,587 --> 00:08:26,004\r\nHey, Red, bump me a deck.\r\n\r\n96\r\n00:08:26,214 --> 00:08:29,508\r\nGet out of my face, man!\r\nYou're into me for five packs already.\r\n\r\n97\r\n00:08:29,717 --> 00:08:30,717\r\n- Four!\r\n- Five!\r\n\r\n98\r\n00:08:31,844 --> 00:08:35,263\r\nRED: There must be a con like me\r\nin every prison in America.\r\n\r\n99\r\n00:08:35,473 --> 00:08:37,265\r\nI'm the guy who can get it for you.\r\n\r\n100\r\n00:08:37,475 --> 00:08:40,602\r\nCigarettes, a bag of reefer,\r\nif that's your thing...\r\n\r\n101\r\n00:08:40,770 --> 00:08:44,231\r\n...a bottle of brandy to celebrate\r\nyour kid's high school graduation.\r\n\r\n102\r\n00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:46,566\r\nDamn near anything within reason.\r\n\r\n103\r\n00:08:46,776 --> 00:08:50,487\r\nYes, sir. I'm a regular Sears and Roebuck.\r\n\r\n104\r\n00:08:51,239 --> 00:08:52,239\r\n[SIREN WAILING]\r\n\r\n105\r\n00:08:53,449 --> 00:08:56,368\r\nSo when Andy Dufresne\r\ncame to me in 1949...\r\n\r\n106\r\n00:08:56,577 --> 00:09:00,121\r\n...and asked me to smuggle\r\nRita Hayworth into the prison for him...\r\n\r\n107\r\n00:09:00,331 --> 00:09:02,624\r\n...I told him, \"No problem.\"\r\n\r\n108\r\n00:09:22,144 --> 00:09:26,314\r\nMAN [OVER INTERCOM]: Officers\r\nto main gate. Officers to main gate.\r\n\r\n109\r\n00:09:26,983 --> 00:09:29,526\r\nSecure main gate.\r\n\r\n110\r\n00:09:44,458 --> 00:09:46,668\r\nRED:\r\nAndy came to Shawshank Prison...\r\n\r\n111\r\n00:09:46,877 --> 00:09:50,755\r\n...in early 1947 for murdering his wife\r\nand the fella she was banging.\r\n\r\n112\r\n00:09:51,090 --> 00:09:55,176\r\nOn the outside, he'd been vice president\r\nof a large Portland bank.\r\n\r\n113\r\n00:09:55,595 --> 00:09:57,387\r\nGood work for a man so young.\r\n\r\n114\r\n00:10:02,727 --> 00:10:04,269\r\nFLOYD:\r\nHey, Red.\r\n\r\n115\r\n00:10:06,022 --> 00:10:07,355\r\n[MEN WHISTLING]\r\n\r\n116\r\n00:10:14,322 --> 00:10:15,572\r\n[MEN CHEERING]\r\n\r\n117\r\n00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:42,390\r\nYou speak English, butt-steak?\r\n\r\n118\r\n00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,476\r\nYou follow this officer.\r\n\r\n119\r\n00:10:55,571 --> 00:10:56,571\r\n[MEN YELLING]\r\n\r\n120\r\n00:10:57,239 --> 00:11:01,493\r\nI never seen such a sorry-looking\r\nheap of maggot shit in all my life.\r\n\r\n121\r\n00:11:01,744 --> 00:11:04,329\r\nMAN:\r\nHey, fish! Come over here!\r\n\r\n122\r\n00:11:27,603 --> 00:11:28,978\r\nTaking bets today, Red?\r\n\r\n123\r\n00:11:29,355 --> 00:11:31,064\r\nSmokes or coin? Bettor's choice.\r\n\r\n124\r\n00:11:31,273 --> 00:11:32,941\r\nSmokes. Put me down for two.\r\n\r\n125\r\n00:11:33,484 --> 00:11:35,068\r\nAll right, who's your horse?\r\n\r\n126\r\n00:11:35,277 --> 00:11:37,028\r\nThat little sack of shit.\r\n\r\n127\r\n00:11:37,822 --> 00:11:41,616\r\n- Eighth. Eighth from the front. He'll be first.\r\n- Oh, bullshit! I'll take that action.\r\n\r\n128\r\n00:11:41,784 --> 00:11:44,327\r\nSNOOZE: Yeah, me too.\r\n- You're out some smokes, son.\r\n\r\n129\r\n00:11:44,495 --> 00:11:46,287\r\nIf you're so smart, you call it.\r\n\r\n130\r\n00:11:46,497 --> 00:11:49,582\r\nI'll take the chubby fat-ass there.\r\n\r\n131\r\n00:11:49,792 --> 00:11:52,377\r\nThe fifth one.\r\nPut me down for a quarter deck.\r\n\r\n132\r\n00:11:54,130 --> 00:11:55,338\r\nMAN:\r\nFresh Fish!\r\n\r\n133\r\n00:11:55,589 --> 00:11:57,298\r\nFresh fish today!\r\n\r\n134\r\n00:11:58,050 --> 00:11:59,509\r\nWe're reeling them in!\r\n\r\n135\r\n00:12:00,177 --> 00:12:03,847\r\nRED: I admit I didn't think much of Andy\r\nfirst time I laid eyes on him.\r\n\r\n136\r\n00:12:04,390 --> 00:12:07,308\r\nLooked like a stiff breeze\r\nwould blow him over.\r\n\r\n137\r\n00:12:07,643 --> 00:12:09,769\r\nThat was my first impression of the man.\r\n\r\n138\r\n00:12:09,979 --> 00:12:11,396\r\nFLOYD:\r\nWhat do you say?\r\n\r\n139\r\n00:12:11,605 --> 00:12:14,899\r\nThat tall drink of water\r\nwith the silver spoon up his ass.\r\n\r\n140\r\n00:12:15,109 --> 00:12:17,235\r\nThat guy? Never happen.\r\n\r\n141\r\n00:12:17,445 --> 00:12:19,696\r\n- Ten cigarettes.\r\nSNOOZE: That's a rich bet.\r\n\r\n142\r\n00:12:19,905 --> 00:12:21,990\r\nWho's going to prove me wrong?\r\n\r\n143\r\n00:12:22,158 --> 00:12:23,992\r\nHeywood? Jigger?\r\n\r\n144\r\n00:12:24,285 --> 00:12:25,577\r\nSkeets?\r\n\r\n145\r\n00:12:25,786 --> 00:12:27,120\r\nFloyd!\r\n\r\n146\r\n00:12:28,038 --> 00:12:30,123\r\nFour brave souls.\r\n\r\n147\r\n00:12:30,332 --> 00:12:33,084\r\nMAN [OVER INTERCOM]:\r\nReturn to your cellblocks for evening count.\r\n\r\n148\r\n00:12:33,294 --> 00:12:36,588\r\nAll prisoners, return to your cellblocks.\r\n\r\n149\r\n00:12:56,984 --> 00:12:59,611\r\nHADLEY:\r\nTurn to the right! Eyes front.\r\n\r\n150\r\n00:13:12,708 --> 00:13:15,293\r\nThis is Mr. Hadley.\r\nHe's captain of the guards.\r\n\r\n151\r\n00:13:15,503 --> 00:13:17,587\r\nI'm Mr. Norton, the warden.\r\n\r\n152\r\n00:13:17,797 --> 00:13:20,006\r\nYou are convicted felons.\r\n\r\n153\r\n00:13:20,299 --> 00:13:22,300\r\nThat's why they've sent you to me.\r\n\r\n154\r\n00:13:22,885 --> 00:13:24,260\r\nRule number one:\r\n\r\n155\r\n00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:25,970\r\nNo blasphemy.\r\n\r\n156\r\n00:13:26,472 --> 00:13:29,891\r\nI'll not have the Lord's name\r\ntaken in vain in my prison.\r\n\r\n157\r\n00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:31,309\r\nThe other rules...\r\n\r\n158\r\n00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:34,813\r\n...you'll figure out as you go along.\r\nAny questions?\r\n\r\n159\r\n00:13:35,189 --> 00:13:36,231\r\nWhen do we eat?\r\n\r\n160\r\n00:13:44,907 --> 00:13:46,950\r\nHADLEY:\r\nYou eat when we say you eat.\r\n\r\n161\r\n00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:50,411\r\nYou shit when we say you shit,\r\nand piss when we say you piss.\r\n\r\n162\r\n00:13:50,621 --> 00:13:53,456\r\nYou got that,\r\nyou maggot-dick motherfucker?\r\n\r\n163\r\n00:13:55,334 --> 00:13:56,709\r\nOn your feet.\r\n\r\n164\r\n00:13:56,919 --> 00:13:58,670\r\nNORTON:\r\nI believe in two things:\r\n\r\n165\r\n00:13:58,879 --> 00:14:01,339\r\nDiscipline and the Bible.\r\n\r\n166\r\n00:14:01,841 --> 00:14:03,925\r\nHere, you'll receive both.\r\n\r\n167\r\n00:14:04,677 --> 00:14:06,845\r\nPut your trust in the Lord.\r\n\r\n168\r\n00:14:07,429 --> 00:14:09,681\r\nYour ass belongs to me.\r\n\r\n169\r\n00:14:11,517 --> 00:14:13,434\r\nWelcome to Shawshank.\r\n\r\n170\r\n00:14:18,607 --> 00:14:19,941\r\nUnhook them.\r\n\r\n171\r\n00:14:25,364 --> 00:14:26,781\r\nTurn around.\r\n\r\n172\r\n00:14:33,622 --> 00:14:35,039\r\nThat's enough.\r\n\r\n173\r\n00:14:35,958 --> 00:14:37,959\r\nMove to the end of the cage.\r\n\r\n174\r\n00:14:38,961 --> 00:14:41,462\r\nTurn around. Delouse him.\r\n\r\n175\r\n00:14:43,632 --> 00:14:44,883\r\nTurn around.\r\n\r\n176\r\n00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:50,430\r\nMove out of the cage.\r\nPick up your clothes and Bible.\r\n\r\n177\r\n00:14:50,639 --> 00:14:51,973\r\nNext man up!\r\n\r\n178\r\n00:14:54,268 --> 00:14:56,978\r\nTo the right. Right. Right. Right.\r\n\r\n179\r\n00:14:57,521 --> 00:14:58,771\r\nLeft. Left.\r\n\r\n180\r\n00:14:59,148 --> 00:15:02,984\r\nRED: The first night's the toughest.\r\nNo doubt about it.\r\n\r\n181\r\n00:15:03,402 --> 00:15:06,529\r\nThey march you in\r\nnaked as the day you were born...\r\n\r\n182\r\n00:15:06,739 --> 00:15:10,533\r\n...skin burning and half-blind\r\nfrom that delousing shit.\r\n\r\n183\r\n00:15:11,201 --> 00:15:13,620\r\nAnd when they put you in that cell...\r\n\r\n184\r\n00:15:13,829 --> 00:15:16,164\r\n...and those bars slam 