\nWhy don't you give him some of your\r\ncigarettes instead? Lucky fuck!\r\n\r\n278\r\n00:22:50,243 --> 00:22:51,786\r\nHey, Tyrell.\r\n\r\n279\r\n00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:54,121\r\nYou pull infirmary duty this week?\r\n\r\n280\r\n00:22:55,082 --> 00:22:56,665\r\nHow's that horse of mine doing anyway?\r\n\r\n281\r\n00:22:57,084 --> 00:22:58,209\r\nDead.\r\n\r\n282\r\n00:22:59,044 --> 00:23:01,253\r\nHadley busted his head up pretty good.\r\n\r\n283\r\n00:23:01,463 --> 00:23:03,631\r\nDoc had gone home for the night.\r\n\r\n284\r\n00:23:04,132 --> 00:23:06,425\r\nPoor bastard lay there\r\ntill this morning.\r\n\r\n285\r\n00:23:06,635 --> 00:23:09,095\r\nBy then, there wasn't nothing\r\nwe could do.\r\n\r\n286\r\n00:23:15,394 --> 00:23:16,685\r\nWhat was his name?\r\n\r\n287\r\n00:23:20,065 --> 00:23:21,315\r\nWhat'd you say?\r\n\r\n288\r\n00:23:23,235 --> 00:23:25,653\r\nI was just wondering\r\nif anyone knew his name.\r\n\r\n289\r\n00:23:26,321 --> 00:23:29,073\r\nWhat the fuck do you care, new fish?\r\n\r\n290\r\n00:23:30,075 --> 00:23:33,202\r\nDoesn't fucking matter\r\nwhat his name was. He's dead.\r\n\r\n291\r\n00:23:52,681 --> 00:23:54,306\r\nHey.\r\n\r\n292\r\n00:23:55,267 --> 00:23:57,268\r\nAnybody come at you yet?\r\n\r\n293\r\n00:23:59,396 --> 00:24:01,230\r\nAnybody get to you yet?\r\n\r\n294\r\n00:24:02,899 --> 00:24:05,443\r\nHey, we all need friends in here.\r\n\r\n295\r\n00:24:05,735 --> 00:24:07,403\r\nI could be a friend to you.\r\n\r\n296\r\n00:24:10,657 --> 00:24:12,116\r\nHey.\r\n\r\n297\r\n00:24:16,621 --> 00:24:18,038\r\nHard to get.\r\n\r\n298\r\n00:24:20,125 --> 00:24:21,625\r\nI like that.\r\n\r\n299\r\n00:24:28,550 --> 00:24:31,802\r\nRED: Andy kept pretty much\r\nto himself at first.\r\n\r\n300\r\n00:24:32,137 --> 00:24:34,096\r\nI guess he had a lot on his mind...\r\n\r\n301\r\n00:24:34,556 --> 00:24:37,391\r\n...trying to adapt\r\nto life on the inside.\r\n\r\n302\r\n00:24:38,101 --> 00:24:41,312\r\nWasn't until a month went by\r\nthat he finally opened his mouth...\r\n\r\n303\r\n00:24:41,521 --> 00:24:43,898\r\n...to say more than two words\r\nto somebody.\r\n\r\n304\r\n00:24:45,066 --> 00:24:46,650\r\nAs it turned out...\r\n\r\n305\r\n00:24:47,110 --> 00:24:48,986\r\n...that somebody was me.\r\n\r\n306\r\n00:24:52,157 --> 00:24:55,784\r\nMAN [ON SPEAKER]: Officers Russell\r\nand Berwell, report to duty officer.\r\n\r\n307\r\n00:24:55,952 --> 00:24:57,578\r\nRussell and Berwell, report to...\r\n\r\n308\r\n00:24:57,746 --> 00:24:59,538\r\nI'm Andy Dufresne.\r\n\r\n309\r\n00:25:00,749 --> 00:25:02,500\r\nWife-killing banker.\r\n\r\n310\r\n00:25:04,753 --> 00:25:06,086\r\nWhy'd you do it?\r\n\r\n311\r\n00:25:06,505 --> 00:25:08,589\r\nI didn't, since you ask.\r\n\r\n312\r\n00:25:09,174 --> 00:25:11,008\r\nYou're going to fit right in.\r\n\r\n313\r\n00:25:11,259 --> 00:25:13,928\r\nEverybody in here's innocent.\r\nDidn't you know that?\r\n\r\n314\r\n00:25:14,554 --> 00:25:17,765\r\n- What you in here for?\r\n- Didn't do it. Lawyer fucked me.\r\n\r\n315\r\n00:25:20,769 --> 00:25:23,354\r\nRumor has it you're a real cold fish.\r\n\r\n316\r\n00:25:23,563 --> 00:25:27,149\r\nYou think your shit smells\r\nsweeter than most. Is that right?\r\n\r\n317\r\n00:25:27,359 --> 00:25:28,817\r\nWhat do you think?\r\n\r\n318\r\n00:25:29,194 --> 00:25:32,279\r\nTo tell you the truth,\r\nI haven't made up my mind.\r\n\r\n319\r\n00:25:33,406 --> 00:25:36,200\r\nI understand you're a man\r\nthat knows how to get things.\r\n\r\n320\r\n00:25:37,160 --> 00:25:40,454\r\nI'm known to locate certain things\r\nfrom time to time.\r\n\r\n321\r\n00:25:40,664 --> 00:25:42,623\r\nI wonder if you might get me\r\na rock hammer.\r\n\r\n322\r\n00:25:42,791 --> 00:25:45,251\r\n- A what?\r\n- A rock hammer.\r\n\r\n323\r\n00:25:45,627 --> 00:25:48,295\r\n- What is it and why?\r\n- What do you care?\r\n\r\n324\r\n00:25:49,631 --> 00:25:52,341\r\nWell, if it was a toothbrush, I wouldn't ask.\r\nI'd quote a price.\r\n\r\n325\r\n00:25:52,551 --> 00:25:54,969\r\nBut then a toothbrush\r\nis a non-lethal object, isn't it?\r\n\r\n326\r\n00:25:56,555 --> 00:25:57,972\r\nFair enough.\r\n\r\n327\r\n00:25:58,390 --> 00:26:01,016\r\nA rock hammer is about\r\nsix or seven inches long.\r\n\r\n328\r\n00:26:01,226 --> 00:26:03,561\r\n- Looks like a miniature pickax.\r\n- Pickax?\r\n\r\n329\r\n00:26:03,770 --> 00:26:05,980\r\n- For rocks.\r\n- Rocks.\r\n\r\n330\r\n00:26:07,566 --> 00:26:08,816\r\nQuartz?\r\n\r\n331\r\n00:26:09,693 --> 00:26:11,402\r\nQuartz.\r\n\r\n332\r\n00:26:12,737 --> 00:26:16,198\r\nAnd some mica, shale...\r\n\r\n333\r\n00:26:17,450 --> 00:26:18,701\r\n...limestone.\r\n\r\n334\r\n00:26:18,952 --> 00:26:20,077\r\nSo?\r\n\r\n335\r\n00:26:20,996 --> 00:26:22,830\r\nSo I'm a rock hound.\r\n\r\n336\r\n00:26:23,290 --> 00:26:26,375\r\nAt least I was in my old life.\r\nI'd like to be again on a limited basis.\r\n\r\n337\r\n00:26:26,668 --> 00:26:29,753\r\nOr maybe you'd like to sink your toy\r\ninto somebody's skull.\r\n\r\n338\r\n00:26:29,921 --> 00:26:32,840\r\nNo, sir. No, I have no enemies here.\r\n\r\n339\r\n00:26:33,008 --> 00:26:35,342\r\nNo? Wait a while.\r\n\r\n340\r\n00:26:36,970 --> 00:26:38,554\r\nWord gets around.\r\n\r\n341\r\n00:26:39,222 --> 00:26:41,724\r\nThe Sisters have taken\r\nquite a liking to you.\r\n\r\n342\r\n00:26:43,101 --> 00:26:44,893\r\nEspecially Bogs.\r\n\r\n343\r\n00:26:45,895 --> 00:26:49,356\r\nDon't suppose it would help any\r\nif I explained to them I'm not homosexual.\r\n\r\n344\r\n00:26:49,524 --> 00:26:50,983\r\nRED:\r\nNeither are they.\r\n\r\n345\r\n00:26:51,192 --> 00:26:54,653\r\nYou have to be human first.\r\nThey don't qualify.\r\n\r\n346\r\n00:26:59,159 --> 00:27:03,537\r\nBull queers take by force.\r\nThat's all they want or understand.\r\n\r\n347\r\n00:27:03,747 --> 00:27:07,291\r\nIf I were you, I'd grow eyes\r\nin the back of my head.\r\n\r\n348\r\n00:27:07,500 --> 00:27:10,252\r\n- Thanks for the advice.\r\n- Well, that's free.\r\n\r\n349\r\n00:27:10,587 --> 00:27:12,546\r\nYou understand my concern.\r\n\r\n350\r\n00:27:12,756 --> 00:27:16,091\r\nIf there's any trouble,\r\nI won't use the rock hammer, okay?\r\n\r\n351\r\n00:27:16,259 --> 00:27:20,346\r\nThen I'd guess you want to escape.\r\nTunnel under the wall, maybe.\r\n\r\n352\r\n00:27:21,222 --> 00:27:22,890\r\nDid I miss something? What's so funny?\r\n\r\n353\r\n00:27:23,308 --> 00:27:26,018\r\nYou'll understand\r\nwhen you see the rock hammer.\r\n\r\n354\r\n00:27:27,854 --> 00:27:30,064\r\nWhat's an item like this usually go for?\r\n\r\n355\r\n00:27:30,273 --> 00:27:32,775\r\nSeven dollars in any rock-and-gem shop.\r\n\r\n356\r\n00:27:33,276 --> 00:27:35,736\r\nMy normal markup's 20 percent.\r\n\r\n357\r\n00:27:35,945 --> 00:27:38,322\r\nBut this is a specialty item.\r\n\r\n358\r\n00:27:38,531 --> 00:27:42,993\r\nRisk goes up, price goes up.\r\nLet's make it an even 10 bucks.\r\n\r\n359\r\n00:27:43,203 --> 00:27:44,536\r\nTen it is.\r\n\r\n360\r\n00:27:46,247 --> 00:27:48,290\r\nWaste of money, if you ask me.\r\n\r\n361\r\n00:27:48,583 --> 00:27:49,875\r\nWhy's that?\r\n\r\n362\r\n00:27:51,252 --> 00:27:54,296\r\nFolks around this joint\r\nlove surprise inspections.\r\n\r\n363\r\n00:27:55,924 --> 00:27:57,883\r\nThey find it, you're going to lose it.\r\n\r\n364\r\n00:27:58,093 --> 00:28:00,177\r\nIf they do catch you with it,\r\nyou don't know me.\r\n\r\n365\r\n00:28:00,387 --> 00:28:02,596\r\nYou mention my name,\r\nwe never do business again.\r\n\r\n366\r\n00:28:03,098 --> 00:28:06,225\r\nNot for shoelaces or a stick of gum.\r\nNow you got that?\r\n\r\n367\r\n00:28:07,060 --> 00:28:08,602\r\nI understand.\r\n\r\n368\r\n00:28:09,813 --> 00:28:11,939\r\nThank you, Mr...\r\n\r\n369\r\n00:28:12,107 --> 00:28:13,148\r\nRed.\r\n\r\n370\r\n00:28:13,900 --> 00:28:15,192\r\n- Name's Red.\r\n- Red.\r\n\r\n371\r\n00:28:16,611 --> 00:28:18,278\r\nWhy do they call you that?\r\n\r\n372\r\n00:28:22,033 --> 00:28:24,034\r\nMaybe it's because I'm Irish.\r\n\r\n373\r\n00:28:32,210 --> 00:28:35,087\r\nRED: I could see why some of the boys\r\ntook him for snobby.\r\n\r\n374\r\n00:28:35,964 --> 00:28:38,382\r\nHe had a quiet way about him...\r\n\r\n375\r\n00:28:38,717 --> 00:28:42,886\r\n...a walk and a talk that just\r\nwasn't normal around here.\r\n\r\n376\r\n00:28:43,221 --> 00:28:44,680\r\nHe strolled...\r\n\r\n377\r\n00:28:44,889 --> 00:28:49,101\r\n...like a man in the park without a care\r\nor a worry in the world.\r\n\r\n378\r\n00:28:49,310 --> 00:28:53,981\r\nLike he had on an invisible coat\r\nthat would shield him from this place.\r\n\r\n379\r\n00:28:54,315 --> 00:28:58,152\r\nYeah, I think it would be fair to say...\r\n\r\n380\r\n00:28:58,403 --> 00:29:00,654\r\n...I liked Andy from the start.\r\n\r\n381\r\n00:29:02,407 --> 00:29:05,993\r\nMAN: Let's go! Some of us\r\ngot a schedule to keep.\r\n\r\n382\r\n00:29:09,330 --> 00:29:11,832\r\nMove it! Come on, move it!\r\n\r\n383\r\n00:29:14,419 --> 00:29:17,337\r\nHow you doing?\r\nHow's the wife treating you?\r\n\r\n384\r\n00:29:29,017 --> 00:29:30,976\r\nMAN:\r\nKeep it moving.\r\n\r\n385\r\n00:29:34,272 --> 00:29:36,023\r\nRed.\r\n\r\n386\r\n00:29:55,502 --> 00:29:56,960\r\nRED:\r\nAndy was right.\r\n\r\n387\r\n00:29:57,212 --> 00:29:59,421\r\nI finally got the joke.\r\n\r\n388\r\n00:29:59,714 --> 00:30:02,132\r\nIt would take a man about 600 years...\r\n\r\n389\r\n00:30:02,342 --> 00:30:04,802\r\n...to tunnel under the wall\r\nwith one of these.\r\n\r\n390\r\n00:30:05,887 --> 00:30:08,388\r\n[WHEELS SQUEAKING]\r\n\r\n391\r\n00:30:08,556 --> 00:30:11,016\r\n- Book?\r\nMAN 1: Not today.\r\n\r\n392\r\n00:30:17,065 --> 00:30:19,066\r\n- Book?\r\nMAN 2: No.\r\n\r\n393\r\n00:30:20,777 --> 00:30:22,945\r\nRED:\r\nHey, Brooksie.\r\n\r\n394\r\n00:30:25,406 --> 00:30:27,574\r\nDelivery for Dufresne.\r\n\r\n395\r\n00:30:34,624 --> 00:30:36,750\r\nBOOKS: Book?\r\nMAN 3: Pass.\r\n\r\n396\r\n00:30:38,378 --> 00:30:39,878\r\nBOOKS:\r\nBook?\r\n\r\n397\r\n00:30:43,049 --> 00:30:46,844\r\nDufresne, here's your book.\r\n\r\n398\r\n00:30:51,850 --> 00:30:53,100\r\nThanks.\r\n\r\n399\r\n00:30:58,106 --> 00:31:03,068\r\nDufresne, we're running low on hexite.\r\nGet on back and fetch us up some.\r\n\r\n400\r\n00:31:40,356 --> 00:31:41,940\r\nThis will blind you.\r\n\r\n401\r\n00:31:42,317 --> 00:31:44,693\r\nHoney, hush.\r\n\r\n402\r\n00:31:57,248 --> 00:31:59,207\r\nThat's it. You fight!\r\n\r\n403\r\n00:31:59,417 --> 00:32:00,876\r\nBetter that way.\r\n\r\n404\r\n00:32:01,169 --> 00:32:03,670\r\n[ANDY SCREAMING AND GROANING]\r\n\r\n405\r\n00:32:09,135 --> 00:32:12,220\r\nRED: I wish I could tell you\r\nthat Andy fought the good fight...\r\n\r\n406\r\n00:32:12,430 --> 00:32:14,431\r\n...and the Sisters let him be.\r\n\r\n407\r\n00:32:15,016 --> 00:32:16,850\r\nI wish I could tell you that...\r\n\r\n408\r\n00:32:17,018 --> 00:32:20,020\r\n...but prison is no fairy-tale world.\r\n\r\n409\r\n00:32:21,147 --> 00:32:23,106\r\nHe never said who did it.\r\n\r\n410\r\n00:32:23,358 --> 00:32:24,942\r\nBut we all knew.\r\n\r\n411\r\n00:32:26,527 --> 00:32:28,403\r\n[HORN BUZZING]\r\n\r\n412\r\n00:32:29,781 --> 00:32:32,282\r\nThings went on like that for a while.\r\n\r\n413\r\n00:32:32,700 --> 00:32:35,202\r\nPrison life consists of routine...\r\n\r\n414\r\n00:32:35,453 --> 00:32:37,412\r\n...and then more routine.\r\n\r\n415\r\n00:32:39,916 --> 00:32:43,460\r\nEvery so often, Andy would show up\r\nwith fresh bruises.\r\n\r\n416\r\n00:32:44,921 --> 00:32:46,755\r\nThe Sisters kept at him.\r\n\r\n417\r\n00:32:47,006 --> 00:32:49,049\r\nSometimes he was able\r\nto fight them off.\r\n\r\n418\r\n00:32:49,258 --> 00:32:50,759\r\nSometimes not.\r\n\r\n419\r\n00:32:51,928 --> 00:32:54,096\r\nAnd that's how it went for Andy.\r\n\r\n420\r\n00:32:54,681 --> 00:32:56,431\r\nThat was his routine.\r\n\r\n421\r\n00:32:57,266 --> 00:33:00,727\r\nI do believe those first two years\r\nwere the worst for him.\r\n\r\n422\r\n00:33:01,229 --> 00:33:04,564\r\nAnd I also believe\r\nif things had gone on that way...\r\n\r\n423\r\n00:33:04,899 --> 00:33:07,359\r\n...this place would have\r\ngot the best of him.\r\n\r\n424\r\n00:33:08,111 --> 00:33:10,904\r\nBut then, in the spring of 1949...\r\n\r\n425\r\n00:33:11,114 --> 00:33:13,031\r\n...the powers that be decided that:\r\n\r\n426\r\n00:33:13,241 --> 00:33:16,576\r\nThe roof of the license-plate factory\r\nneeds resurfacing.\r\n\r\n427\r\n00:33:16,744 --> 00:33:19,955\r\nI need a dozen volunteers\r\nfor a week's work.\r\n\r\n428\r\n00:33:20,665 --> 00:33:22,124\r\nAs you know...\r\n\r\n429\r\n00:33:22,875 --> 00:33:26,420\r\n...special detail carries with it\r\nspecial privileges.\r\n\r\n430\r\n00:33:26,629 --> 00:33:29,047\r\nRED:\r\nIt was outdoor detail...\r\n\r\n431\r\n00:33:29,424 --> 00:33:33,719\r\n...and May is one damned fine month\r\nto be working outdoors.\r\n\r\n432\r\n00:33:34,178 --> 00:33:35,262\r\nMAN:\r\nStay in line there.\r\n\r\n433\r\n00:33:35,471 --> 00:33:38,640\r\nRED: More than 100 men\r\nvolunteered for the job.\r\n\r\n434\r\n00:33:42,937 --> 00:33:45,939\r\n\"Wallace E. Unger.\r\n\r\n435\r\n00:33:46,441 --> 00:33:48,775\r\nEllis Redding.\"\r\n\r\n436\r\n00:33:48,985 --> 00:33:50,569\r\nRED:\r\nWouldn't you know it?\r\n\r\n437\r\n00:33:50,987 --> 00:33:54,281\r\nMe and some fellows I know\r\nwere among the names called.\r\n\r\n438\r\n00:33:54,490 --> 00:33:56,491\r\nGUARD:\r\n\"Andrew Dufresne.\"\r\n\r\n439\r\n00:33:56,909 --> 00:33:59,828\r\nRED: It only cost us\r\na pack of smokes per man.\r\n\r\n440\r\n00:34:00,329 --> 00:34:02,789\r\nI made my usual 20 percent, of course.\r\n\r\n441\r\n00:34:02,999 --> 00:34:06,460\r\nHADLEY: So this big-shot lawyer\r\ncalls me long-distance from Texas.\r\n\r\n442\r\n00:34:06,669 --> 00:34:08,253\r\nI say, \"Yeah?\"\r\n\r\n443\r\n00:34:08,504 --> 00:34:12,132\r\nHe says, \"Sorry to inform you,\r\nbut your brother just died.\"\r\n\r\n444\r\n00:34:12,341 --> 00:34:16,261\r\n- I'm sorry to hear that.\r\n- I'm not. He was an asshole.\r\n\r\n445\r\n00:34:16,471 --> 00:34:18,638\r\nRan off years ago.\r\nFigured him for dead.\r\n\r\n446\r\n00:34:18,848 --> 00:34:21,141\r\nSo anyway, this lawyer fellow says to me:\r\n\r\n447\r\n00:34:21,350 --> 00:34:25,479\r\n\"Your brother died a rich man.\"\r\nOil wells and shit. Close to a million bucks.\r\n\r\n448\r\n00:34:26,147 --> 00:34:28,023\r\nTROUT: A million bucks?\r\nHADLEY: Yeah.\r\n\r\n449\r\n00:34:28,316 --> 00:34:32,819\r\n- Incredible how lucky some assholes get.\r\n- You going to see any of that?\r\n\r\n450\r\n00:34:33,446 --> 00:34:36,198\r\nThirty-five thousand.\r\nThat's what he left me.\r\n\r\n451\r\n00:34:36,407 --> 00:34:38,158\r\nTROUT: Dollars?\r\n- Yep.\r\n\r\n452\r\n00:34:38,326 --> 00:34:41,328\r\nHoly shit, that's great!\r\nThat's like winning the sweepstakes.\r\n\r\n453\r\n00:34:41,662 --> 00:34:42,829\r\nIsn't it?\r\n\r\n454\r\n00:34:42,997 --> 00:34:45,957\r\nDumb-shit, what do you think\r\nthe government is gonna do to me?\r\n\r\n455\r\n00:34:46,167 --> 00:34:48,502\r\nTake a big wet bite\r\nout of my ass is what.\r\n\r\n456\r\n00:34:49,295 --> 00:34:50,629\r\nPoor Byron.\r\n\r\n457\r\n00:34:51,506 --> 00:34:54,674\r\nTerrible fucking luck, huh?\r\nCrying shame.\r\n\r\n458\r\n00:34:54,884 --> 00:34:57,177\r\nSome people really got it awful.\r\n\r\n459\r\n00:34:57,428 --> 00:34:58,804\r\nAndy, are you nuts?\r\n\r\n460\r\n00:34:59,013 --> 00:35:00,889\r\nKeep your eyes on your mop, man! Andy.\r\n\r\n461\r\n00:35:01,099 --> 00:35:04,059\r\nTROUT: You'll pay some tax,\r\nbut you'll still end up...\r\n\r\n462\r\n00:35:04,268 --> 00:35:07,062\r\nYeah, yeah, maybe enough to buy\r\na new car, and then what?\r\n\r\n463\r\n00:35:07,271 --> 00:35:09,439\r\nI got to pay tax on the car. Repair...\r\n\r\n464\r\n00:35:09,690 --> 00:35:13,401\r\n...maintenance, kids pestering you\r\nto take them for a ride all the time.\r\n\r\n465\r\n00:35:13,653 --> 00:35:17,322\r\nThen if you figure your tax wrong,\r\nyou pay out of your own pocket.\r\n\r\n466\r\n00: