y have to pry\r\nthe victim's jaws open...\r\n\r\n605\r\n00:43:57,509 --> 00:43:58,885\r\n...with a crowbar.\r\n\r\n606\r\n00:44:01,847 --> 00:44:03,389\r\nWhere do you get this shit?\r\n\r\n607\r\n00:44:03,557 --> 00:44:04,974\r\nI read it.\r\n\r\n608\r\n00:44:06,393 --> 00:44:09,062\r\nYou know how to read,\r\nyou ignorant fuck?\r\n\r\n609\r\n00:44:10,731 --> 00:44:12,023\r\nHoney.\r\n\r\n610\r\n00:44:13,734 --> 00:44:15,485\r\nYou shouldn't!\r\n\r\n611\r\n00:44:18,155 --> 00:44:21,074\r\nRED:\r\nBogs didn't put anything in Andy's mouth.\r\n\r\n612\r\n00:44:21,325 --> 00:44:23,409\r\nAnd neither did his friends.\r\n\r\n613\r\n00:44:23,827 --> 00:44:27,664\r\nWhat they did do is beat him\r\nwithin an inch of his life.\r\n\r\n614\r\n00:44:28,332 --> 00:44:30,833\r\nAndy spent a month in the infirmary.\r\n\r\n615\r\n00:44:31,627 --> 00:44:34,170\r\nBogs spent a week in the hole.\r\n\r\n616\r\n00:44:38,258 --> 00:44:39,759\r\nTime's up, Bogs.\r\n\r\n617\r\n00:44:43,597 --> 00:44:45,264\r\nIt's your world, boss.\r\n\r\n618\r\n00:44:48,519 --> 00:44:51,312\r\nMAN [ON SPEAKER]: Return to\r\nyour cellblocks for evening count.\r\n\r\n619\r\n00:44:51,522 --> 00:44:54,190\r\nAll prisoners report for lockdown.\r\n\r\n620\r\n00:45:09,123 --> 00:45:10,123\r\nWhat?\r\n\r\n621\r\n00:45:12,126 --> 00:45:14,585\r\n[GASPING]\r\n\r\n622\r\n00:45:22,803 --> 00:45:25,304\r\nGUARD: Where's he going?\r\nHADLEY: Grab his ankles.\r\n\r\n623\r\n00:45:28,642 --> 00:45:32,395\r\nNo! No! Help me!\r\n\r\n624\r\n00:45:32,604 --> 00:45:35,064\r\n[BOGS GROANING]\r\n\r\n625\r\n00:45:36,066 --> 00:45:38,651\r\nRED: Two things never happened again\r\nafter that.\r\n\r\n626\r\n00:45:38,944 --> 00:45:42,071\r\nThe Sisters never\r\nlaid a finger on Andy again.\r\n\r\n627\r\n00:45:42,906 --> 00:45:45,408\r\nAnd Bogs never walked again.\r\n\r\n628\r\n00:45:46,577 --> 00:45:50,079\r\nThey transferred him\r\nto a minimum-security hospital upstate.\r\n\r\n629\r\n00:45:50,289 --> 00:45:52,790\r\nTo my knowledge,\r\nhe lived out the rest of his days...\r\n\r\n630\r\n00:45:52,958 --> 00:45:55,084\r\n...drinking his food through a straw.\r\n\r\n631\r\n00:45:56,086 --> 00:46:00,173\r\nAndy could use a nice \"welcome back\"\r\nwhen he gets out of the infirmary.\r\n\r\n632\r\n00:46:01,925 --> 00:46:03,509\r\nSounds good to us.\r\n\r\n633\r\n00:46:03,761 --> 00:46:06,262\r\nI figure we owe him that much\r\nfor the beer.\r\n\r\n634\r\n00:46:07,014 --> 00:46:09,265\r\nThe man likes to play chess.\r\n\r\n635\r\n00:46:09,767 --> 00:46:11,684\r\nLet's get him some rocks.\r\n\r\n636\r\n00:46:44,301 --> 00:46:45,551\r\nGuys!\r\n\r\n637\r\n00:46:46,303 --> 00:46:47,386\r\nI got one.\r\n\r\n638\r\n00:46:47,554 --> 00:46:49,055\r\nI got one. Look!\r\n\r\n639\r\n00:46:50,974 --> 00:46:55,061\r\nHeywood, that isn't soapstone!\r\nAnd it ain't alabaster either.\r\n\r\n640\r\n00:46:55,229 --> 00:46:57,146\r\nWhat are you, a fucking geologist?\r\n\r\n641\r\n00:46:57,356 --> 00:46:59,065\r\nSNOOZE:\r\nHe's right. It ain't.\r\n\r\n642\r\n00:46:59,274 --> 00:47:02,193\r\n- What the hell is it then?\r\nRED: It's a horse apple.\r\n\r\n643\r\n00:47:03,153 --> 00:47:05,571\r\n- Bullshit!\r\nRED: No, horseshit.\r\n\r\n644\r\n00:47:05,739 --> 00:47:07,240\r\nPetrified.\r\n\r\n645\r\n00:47:12,746 --> 00:47:14,747\r\nOh, Jesus.\r\n\r\n646\r\n00:47:16,250 --> 00:47:17,416\r\nDamn!\r\n\r\n647\r\n00:47:17,751 --> 00:47:21,963\r\nRED: Despite a few hitches,\r\nthe boys came through in fine style.\r\n\r\n648\r\n00:47:22,172 --> 00:47:24,173\r\nAnd by the weekend\r\nhe was due back...\r\n\r\n649\r\n00:47:24,383 --> 00:47:28,094\r\n...we had enough rocks saved up\r\nto keep him busy till rapture.\r\n\r\n650\r\n00:47:28,929 --> 00:47:31,430\r\nAlso got a big shipment in that week.\r\n\r\n651\r\n00:47:31,682 --> 00:47:32,807\r\nCigarettes...\r\n\r\n652\r\n00:47:33,016 --> 00:47:34,058\r\n...chewing gum...\r\n\r\n653\r\n00:47:34,268 --> 00:47:35,726\r\n...sipping whiskey...\r\n\r\n654\r\n00:47:35,936 --> 00:47:39,313\r\n...playing cards with naked ladies\r\non them. You name it.\r\n\r\n655\r\n00:47:39,523 --> 00:47:42,275\r\nAnd, of course, the most important item:\r\n\r\n656\r\n00:47:44,111 --> 00:47:46,195\r\nRita Hayworth herself.\r\n\r\n657\r\n00:48:20,355 --> 00:48:23,107\r\nGUARD 1: Okay, look alive!\r\nGUARD 2: Open all tiers.\r\n\r\n658\r\n00:48:23,317 --> 00:48:25,568\r\nHeads up. They're tossing the cells.\r\n\r\n659\r\n00:48:25,777 --> 00:48:28,487\r\nHeads up. They're tossing the cells!\r\n\r\n660\r\n00:48:30,073 --> 00:48:31,574\r\n119.\r\n\r\n661\r\n00:48:33,410 --> 00:48:35,077\r\n123.\r\n\r\n662\r\n00:48:45,339 --> 00:48:46,339\r\nOn your feet.\r\n\r\n663\r\n00:48:49,009 --> 00:48:50,509\r\nFace the wall.\r\n\r\n664\r\n00:49:24,628 --> 00:49:26,545\r\nTurn around and face the warden.\r\n\r\n665\r\n00:49:33,136 --> 00:49:35,221\r\nNORTON:\r\nPleased to see you reading this.\r\n\r\n666\r\n00:49:36,556 --> 00:49:38,474\r\nAny favorite passages?\r\n\r\n667\r\n00:49:39,351 --> 00:49:41,727\r\n\"Watch ye, therefore,\r\nfor ye know not...\r\n\r\n668\r\n00:49:41,895 --> 00:49:44,146\r\n...when the master\r\nof the house cometh.\"\r\n\r\n669\r\n00:49:45,273 --> 00:49:47,441\r\nMark 13:35.\r\n\r\n670\r\n00:49:48,193 --> 00:49:50,069\r\nI've always liked that one.\r\n\r\n671\r\n00:49:50,988 --> 00:49:52,655\r\nBut I prefer:\r\n\r\n672\r\n00:49:53,115 --> 00:49:54,991\r\n\"I am the light of the world.\r\n\r\n673\r\n00:49:55,450 --> 00:49:58,744\r\nYe that followeth me\r\nshall have the light of life.\"\r\n\r\n674\r\n00:49:58,954 --> 00:50:01,580\r\nJohn, chapter 8, verse 12.\r\n\r\n675\r\n00:50:01,873 --> 00:50:03,916\r\nI hear you're good with numbers.\r\n\r\n676\r\n00:50:04,084 --> 00:50:05,084\r\nHow nice.\r\n\r\n677\r\n00:50:06,336 --> 00:50:08,254\r\nMan should have a skill.\r\n\r\n678\r\n00:50:10,799 --> 00:50:11,841\r\nWanna explain this?\r\n\r\n679\r\n00:50:13,010 --> 00:50:17,096\r\nIt's called a rock blanket.\r\nFor shaping and polishing rocks.\r\n\r\n680\r\n00:50:17,514 --> 00:50:19,432\r\nA little hobby of mine.\r\n\r\n681\r\n00:50:30,277 --> 00:50:31,736\r\nIt's pretty clean.\r\n\r\n682\r\n00:50:31,987 --> 00:50:35,114\r\nSome contraband here,\r\nbut nothing to get in a twist over.\r\n\r\n683\r\n00:50:39,453 --> 00:50:41,454\r\nI can't say I approve of this.\r\n\r\n684\r\n00:50:43,081 --> 00:50:44,540\r\nBut I suppose...\r\n\r\n685\r\n00:50:46,626 --> 00:50:48,627\r\n...exceptions can be made.\r\n\r\n686\r\n00:50:58,972 --> 00:51:00,306\r\nHADLEY:\r\nLock them up!\r\n\r\n687\r\n00:51:03,226 --> 00:51:04,810\r\nI almost forgot.\r\n\r\n688\r\n00:51:05,228 --> 00:51:07,396\r\nI'd hate to deprive you of this.\r\n\r\n689\r\n00:51:08,148 --> 00:51:10,066\r\nSalvation lies within.\r\n\r\n690\r\n00:51:10,275 --> 00:51:11,317\r\nYes, sir.\r\n\r\n691\r\n00:51:19,868 --> 00:51:22,453\r\nRED:\r\nTossing cells was just an excuse.\r\n\r\n692\r\n00:51:22,913 --> 00:51:24,163\r\nTruth is...\r\n\r\n693\r\n00:51:24,331 --> 00:51:26,832\r\n...Norton wanted to size Andy up.\r\n\r\n694\r\n00:51:40,514 --> 00:51:42,848\r\nMy wife made that in church group.\r\n\r\n695\r\n00:51:45,519 --> 00:51:46,811\r\nVery nice, sir.\r\n\r\n696\r\n00:51:48,355 --> 00:51:49,855\r\nYou enjoy working the laundry?\r\n\r\n697\r\n00:51:51,525 --> 00:51:53,192\r\nNo, sir. Not especially.\r\n\r\n698\r\n00:51:53,527 --> 00:51:55,986\r\nPerhaps we can find something more...\r\n\r\n699\r\n00:51:56,238 --> 00:51:58,697\r\n...befitting a man of your education.\r\n\r\n700\r\n00:52:02,702 --> 00:52:04,537\r\n[CROWING]\r\n\r\n701\r\n00:52:06,748 --> 00:52:08,249\r\nHey, Jake. Where's Brooks?\r\n\r\n702\r\n00:52:08,875 --> 00:52:12,878\r\nAndy. I thought I heard you out here.\r\n\r\n703\r\n00:52:13,547 --> 00:52:15,089\r\nI've been reassigned to you.\r\n\r\n704\r\n00:52:15,382 --> 00:52:17,716\r\nI know, they told me.\r\n\r\n705\r\n00:52:18,552 --> 00:52:20,594\r\nAin't that a kick in the head?\r\n\r\n706\r\n00:52:20,804 --> 00:52:23,097\r\nWell, I'll give you the dime tour.\r\n\r\n707\r\n00:52:23,306 --> 00:52:24,473\r\nCome on.\r\n\r\n708\r\n00:52:25,892 --> 00:52:27,601\r\nWell, here she is.\r\n\r\n709\r\n00:52:27,811 --> 00:52:29,812\r\nThe Shawshank Prison Library.\r\n\r\n710\r\n00:52:30,480 --> 00:52:32,481\r\nNational Geographics...\r\n\r\n711\r\n00:52:33,400 --> 00:52:36,193\r\n...Reader's Digest condensed books...\r\n\r\n712\r\n00:52:36,403 --> 00:52:37,987\r\n...and Louis L'Amour.\r\n\r\n713\r\n00:52:38,572 --> 00:52:40,406\r\nLook magazine.\r\n\r\n714\r\n00:52:40,740 --> 00:52:43,075\r\nErle Stanley Gardners.\r\n\r\n715\r\n00:52:43,326 --> 00:52:46,787\r\nEvery evening I load up the cart\r\nand make my rounds.\r\n\r\n716\r\n00:52:46,997 --> 00:52:49,665\r\nI enter the names\r\non this clipboard here.\r\n\r\n717\r\n00:52:50,167 --> 00:52:52,751\r\nEasy, peasy, Japanese-y.\r\n\r\n718\r\n00:52:52,919 --> 00:52:56,547\r\n- Any questions?\r\n- Brooks, how long have you been librarian?\r\n\r\n719\r\n00:52:56,756 --> 00:53:01,760\r\nOh... I come here in '05,\r\nand they made me librarian in 1912.\r\n\r\n720\r\n00:53:03,096 --> 00:53:05,264\r\nAnd have you ever had an assistant?\r\n\r\n721\r\n00:53:05,432 --> 00:53:07,933\r\nNo. Not much to it, really.\r\n\r\n722\r\n00:53:08,685 --> 00:53:09,935\r\nWhy me? Why now?\r\n\r\n723\r\n00:53:10,353 --> 00:53:11,645\r\nI don't know.\r\n\r\n724\r\n00:53:11,855 --> 00:53:14,899\r\nBut it'd be nice to have\r\nsome company down here.\r\n\r\n725\r\n00:53:15,150 --> 00:53:16,942\r\nHADLEY:\r\nDufresne!\r\n\r\n726\r\n00:53:26,119 --> 00:53:28,454\r\nThat's him. That's the one.\r\n\r\n727\r\n00:53:36,087 --> 00:53:37,254\r\nI'm Dekins.\r\n\r\n728\r\n00:53:37,631 --> 00:53:39,298\r\nI was...\r\n\r\n729\r\n00:53:39,966 --> 00:53:43,802\r\n...thinking about setting up some kind of\r\ntrust fund for my kids' educations.\r\n\r\n730\r\n00:53:46,097 --> 00:53:49,183\r\nOh. I see.\r\n\r\n731\r\n00:53:50,977 --> 00:53:52,895\r\nWell, um...\r\n\r\n732\r\n00:53:54,314 --> 00:53:57,274\r\nWhy don't we have a seat\r\nand talk it over.\r\n\r\n733\r\n00:53:59,653 --> 00:54:03,447\r\nBrooks, do you have a piece of paper\r\nand a pencil?\r\n\r\n734\r\n00:54:14,793 --> 00:54:16,085\r\nThanks.\r\n\r\n735\r\n00:54:16,753 --> 00:54:17,836\r\nSo...\r\n\r\n736\r\n00:54:19,589 --> 00:54:21,340\r\nMr. Dekins...\r\n\r\n737\r\n00:54:22,175 --> 00:54:24,260\r\nAnd then Andy says, \"Mr. Dekins...\r\n\r\n738\r\n00:54:24,469 --> 00:54:27,471\r\n...do you want your sons\r\nto go to Harvard or Yale?\"\r\n\r\n739\r\n00:54:27,681 --> 00:54:28,722\r\nHe didn't say that!\r\n\r\n740\r\n00:54:29,057 --> 00:54:31,558\r\nAs God as my witness!\r\n\r\n741\r\n00:54:31,851 --> 00:54:33,560\r\nDekins just blinked for a second...\r\n\r\n742\r\n00:54:33,770 --> 00:54:36,897\r\n...then he laughed\r\nand actually shook Andy's hand.\r\n\r\n743\r\n00:54:37,357 --> 00:54:39,692\r\n- My ass!\r\nBROOKS: Shook his hand.\r\n\r\n744\r\n00:54:39,859 --> 00:54:42,736\r\nI tell you, I near soiled myself!\r\n\r\n745\r\n00:54:42,946 --> 00:54:47,199\r\nAll he needed was a suit and tie\r\nand a jiggly hula gal on his desk...\r\n\r\n746\r\n00:54:47,409 --> 00:54:50,035\r\n...he'd have been\r\n\"Mr. Dufresne,\" if you please.\r\n\r\n747\r\n00:54:50,203 --> 00:54:51,870\r\nMaking a few friends, huh, Andy?\r\n\r\n748\r\n00:54:53,164 --> 00:54:54,832\r\nI wouldn't say \"friends.\"\r\n\r\n749\r\n00:54:55,041 --> 00:54:58,877\r\nI'm a convicted murderer\r\nwho provides sound financial planning.\r\n\r\n750\r\n00:54:59,045 --> 00:55:01,380\r\nIt's a wonderful pet to have.\r\n\r\n751\r\n00:55:01,589 --> 00:55:03,382\r\nGot you out of the laundry, though.\r\n\r\n752\r\n00:55:03,925 --> 00:55:05,843\r\nIt might do more than that.\r\n\r\n753\r\n00:55:06,052 --> 00:55:08,762\r\nHow about expanding the library.\r\nGet some new books.\r\n\r\n754\r\n00:55:08,972 --> 00:55:11,557\r\nIf you ask for something,\r\nask for a pool table.\r\n\r\n755\r\n00:55:12,309 --> 00:55:16,270\r\n- Right.\r\n- How do you expect to do that? I mean...\r\n\r\n756\r\n00:55:16,479 --> 00:55:19,440\r\n...get new books in here,\r\n\"Mr. Dufresne, if you please.\"\r\n\r\n757\r\n00:55:19,899 --> 00:55:21,400\r\nI'll ask the warden for funds.\r\n\r\n758\r\n00:55:21,568 --> 00:55:22,693\r\n[MEN CHUCKLING]\r\n\r\n759\r\n00:55:22,861 --> 00:55:27,114\r\nSon, son, son, six wardens have been\r\nthrough here in my tenure, and I've learned...\r\n\r\n760\r\n00:55:27,365 --> 00:55:29,742\r\n...one immutable, universal truth:\r\n\r\n761\r\n00:55:29,909 --> 00:55:32,202\r\nNot one of them born whose asshole...\r\n\r\n762\r\n00:55:32,370 --> 00:55:36,415\r\n...wouldn't pucker up tighter than\r\na snare drum when you ask for funds.\r\n\r\n763\r\n00:55:37,292 --> 00:55:40,210\r\n- The budget's stretched thin as it is.\r\n- I see.\r\n\r\n764\r\n00:55:40,420 --> 00:55:43,839\r\nPerhaps I could write the state senate\r\nand request funds directly from them.\r\n\r\n765\r\n00:55:44,049 --> 00:55:48,135\r\nThey have only three ways to spend\r\nthe taxpayers' money for prisons:\r\n\r\n766\r\n00:55:48,345 --> 00:55:50,763\r\nMore walls, more bars, more guards.\r\n\r\n767\r\n00:55:50,972 --> 00:55:53,640\r\nStill, I'd like to try, with permission.\r\nA letter a week.\r\n\r\n768\r\n00:55:53,850 --> 00:55:56,602\r\n- They can't ignore me forever.\r\n- Sure can.\r\n\r\n769\r\n00:55:56,853 --> 00:55:59,521\r\nBut you write your letters\r\nif it makes you happy.\r\n\r\n770\r\n00:55:59,814 --> 00:56:02,441\r\nI'll even mail them for you. How's that?\r\n\r\n771\r\n00:56:04,110 --> 00:56:06,904\r\nRED: So Andy started writing\r\na letter a week...\r\n\r\n772\r\n00:56:07,113 --> 00:56:08,697\r\n...just like he said.\r\n\r\n773\r\n00:56:12,869 --> 00:56:15,496\r\nAnd, just like Norton said...\r\n\r\n774\r\n00:56:15,705 --> 00:56:17,164\r\n...Andy got no answers.\r\n\r\n775\r\n00:56:25,382 --> 00:56:30,302\r\nThe following April, Andy did tax returns\r\nfor half the guards at Shawshank.\r\n\r\n776\r\n00:56:31,638 --> 00:56:33,889\r\nYear after that, he did them all...\r\n\r\n777\r\n00:56:34,140 --> 00:56:36,058\r\n...including the warden's.\r\n\r\n778\r\n00:56:37,811 --> 00:56:41,271\r\nYear after that,\r\nthey rescheduled the intramural season...\r\n\r\n779\r\n00:56:41,481 --> 00:56:43,899\r\n...to coincide with tax season.\r\n\r\n780\r\n00:56:45,485 --> 00:56:49,947\r\nThe guards on the opposing teams\r\nall remembered to bring their W-2s.\r\n\r\n781\r\n00:56:50,156 --> 00:56:53,951\r\nSo Moresby Prison issued you a gun,\r\nbut you actually paid for it.\r\n\r\n782\r\n00:56:54,160 --> 00:56:55,869\r\nDamn right. The holster too.\r\n\r\n783\r\n00:56:56,079 --> 00:56:58,539\r\nSee, that's tax-deductible.\r\nYou can write that off.\r\n\r\n784\r\n00:56:58,748 --> 00:57:01,792\r\nRED: Yes, sir.\r\nAndy was a regular cottage industry.\r\n\r\n785\r\n00:57:02,502 --> 00:57:07,005\r\nIn fact, it got so busy at tax time,\r\nhe was allowed a staff.\r\n\r\n786\r\n00:57:07,257 --> 00:57:09,716\r\nCould you hand me\r\na stack of 1040s?\r\n\r\n787\r\n00:57:09,926 --> 00:57:14,763\r\nRED: Got me out ofthe wood shop\r\na month out of the year, and that was fine.\r\n\r\n788\r\n00:57:16,015 --> 00:57:19,184\r\nAnd still, he kept sending those letters.\r\n\r\n789\r\n00:57:22,939 --> 00:57:25,774\r\nRed. Red. Andy.\r\n\r\n790\r\n00:57:25,942 --> 00:57:26,984\r\nIt's Brooks.\r\n\r\n791\r\n00:57:28,111 --> 00:57:29,611\r\nRED:\r\nWatch the door.\r\n\r\n792\r\n00:57:29,863 --> 00:57:31,196\r\nPlease, Brooks.\r\n\r\n793\r\n00:57:31,364 --> 00:57:33,240\r\n- Calm the fuck down.\r\n- Stay back!\r\n\r\n794\r\n00:57:33,700 --> 00:57:35,826\r\n- Stay back, goddamn it!\r\n- What's going on?\r\n\r\n795\r\n00:57:35,994 --> 00:57:39,037\r\nYou tell me. One second he's fine,\r\nthen out come the knife.\r\n\r\n796\r\n00:57:39,205 --> 00:57:41,081\r\nBrooks. We can talk about this, right?\r\n\r\n797\r\n00:57:41,249 --> 00:57:45,085\r\nThere's nothing to talk about.\r\nI'll cut his fucking throat.\r\n\r\n798\r\n00:57:45,378 --> 00:57:47,087\r\nWhat's he done to you?\r\n\r\n799\r\n00:57:47,297 --> 00:57:48,964\r\nIt's what they done!\r\n\r\n800\r\n00:57:49,466 --> 00:57:50,716\r\nI got no choice.\r\n\r\n801\r\n00:57:51,217 --> 00:57:53,510\r\nBrooks, you won't hurt Heywood.\r\nWe all know that.\r\n\r\n802\r\n00:57:53,720 --> 00:57:56,180\r\n- Right, Heywood?\r\n- Sure. I know that.\r\n\r\n803\r\n00:57:56,389 --> 00:57:59,725\r\nHe's a friend of yours,\r\nand Brooks is a reasonable man.\r\n\r\n804\r\n00:57:59,893 --> 00:58:01,894\r\n- Right, guys?\r\n- Yes.\r\n\r\n805\r\n00:58:02,061 --> 00:58:04,563\r\nSo put the knife down.\r\nBrooks, look at me.\r\n\r\n806\r\n00:58:04,731 --> 00:58:08,734\r\nPut the knife down. Brooks.\r\n\r\n807\r\n00:58:08,985 --> 00:58:11,069\r\nLook at his neck, for God's sake.\r\n\r\n808\r\n00:58:11,821 --> 00:58:14,156\r\nLook at his neck. He's bleeding.\r\n\r\n809\r\n00:58:15,074 --> 00:58:16,533\r\nIt's the only...\r\n\r\n810\r\n00:58:16,743 --> 00:58:18,785\r\nIt's the only way they'd let me stay.\r\n\r\n811\r\n00:58:19,078 --> 00:58:21,413\r\nCome on, this is crazy.\r\nYou don't want to do this.\r\n\r\n812\r\n00:58:21,664 --> 00:58:23,749\r\nPut it... Put it down.\r\n\r\n813\r\n00:58:23,958 --> 00:58:27,211\r\n[SOBBING]\r\n\r\n814\r\n00:58:31,090 --> 00:58:34,009\r\nHey. Hey. Take it easy.\r\n\r\n815\r\n00:58:34,677 --> 00:58:36,261\r\nYou'll be all right.\r\n\r\n816\r\n00:58:36,429 --> 00:58:38,889\r\nHim? What about me?\r\n\r\n817\r\n00:58:39,098 --> 00:58:41,475\r\nCrazy old fool damn near cut my throat!\r\n\r\n818\r\n00:58:41,684 --> 00:58:43,602\r\nRED:\r\nYou've had worse from shaving.\r\n\r\n819\r\n00:58:43,770 --> 00:58:45,521\r\nWhat did you do to set him off?\r\n\r\n820\r\n00:58:45,688 --> 00:58:48,315\r\nNothing. I come in here to say farewell.\r\n\r\n821\r\n00:58:48,942 --> 00:58:51,610\r\nAin't you heard?\r\nHis parole's come through.\r\n\r\n822\r\n00:58:53,780 --> 00:58:56,740\r\nI just don't understand\r\nwhat happened in there, that's all.\r\n\r\n823\r\n00:58:56,908 --> 00:58:59,743\r\nOld man's crazy as a rat\r\nin a tin shithouse.\r\n\r\n824\r\n00:58:59,953 --> 00:59:01,828\r\nOh, Heywood, that's enough out of you.\r\n\r\n825\r\n00:59:02,038 --> 00:59:04,790\r\n- Heard he had you shitting in your pants.\r\nHEYWOOD: Fuck you.\r\n\r\n826\r\n00:59:05,041 --> 00:59:06,250\r\nKnock it off.\r\n\r\n827\r\n00:59:07,210 --> 00:59:08,627\r\nBrooks ain't no bug.\r\n\r\n828\r\n00:59:08,962 --> 00:59:10,629\r\nHe's just...\r\n\r\n829\r\n00:59:12,465 --> 00:59:14,258\r\nHe's just institutionalized.\r\n\r\n830\r\n00:59:15,635 --> 00:59:17,553\r\n\"Institutionalized,\" my ass.\r\n\r\n831\r\n00:59:17,762 --> 00:59:21,765\r\nThe man's been in here 50 years,\r\nHeywood, 50 years!\r\n\r\n832\r\n00:59:21,975 --> 00:59:23,684\r\nThis is all he knows.\r\n\r\n833\r\n00:59:23,893 --> 00:59:26,186\r\nIn here, he's an important man...\r\n\r\n834\r\n00:59:26,396 --> 00:59:27,479\r\n...an educated man.\r\n\r\n835\r\n00:59:28,314 --> 00:59:30,232\r\nOutside, he's nothing.\r\n\r\n836\r\n00:59:31,109 --> 00:59:34,611\r\nJust a used-up con\r\nwith arthritis in both hands.\r\n\r\n837\r\n00:59:34,821 --> 00:59:37,823\r\nProbably couldn't get a library card\r\nif he tried.\r\n\r\n838\r\n00:59:38,074 --> 00:59:39,825\r\nYou know what I'm trying to say?\r\n\r\n839\r\n00:59:40,076 --> 00:59:42,995\r\nI do believe\r\nyou're talking out of your ass.\r\n\r\n840\r\n00:59:44,247 --> 00:59:46,498\r\nYou believe whatever you want.\r\n\r\n841\r\n00:59:47,083 --> 00:59:49,501\r\nBut I tell you these walls are funny.\r\n\r\n842\r\n00:59:51,087 --> 00:59:52,754\r\nFirst you hate them.\r\n\r\n843\r\n00:59:54,591 --> 00:59:56,508\r\nThen you get used to them.\r\n\r\n844\r\n00:59:58,428 --> 01:00:00,429\r\nEnough time passes...\r\n\r\n845\r\n01:00:01,097 --> 01:00:03,098\r\n...you get so you depend on them.\r\n\r\n846\r\n01:00:04,100 --> 01:00:06,310\r\nThat's \"institutionalized.\"\r\n\r\n847\r\n01:00:06,519 --> 01:00:10,772\r\n- Shit. I could never get like that.\r\n- Oh, yeah?\r\n\r\n848\r\n01:00:11,649 --> 01:00:14,151\r\nWait till you've been here\r\nas long as Brooks.\r\n\r\n849\r\n01:00:14,360 --> 01:00:15,944\r\nGoddamn right.\r\n\r\n850\r\n01:00:18,531 --> 01:00:20,449\r\nThey send you here for life...\r\n\r\n851\r\n01:00:21,117 --> 01:00:23,452\r\n...that's exactly what they take.\r\n\r\n852\r\n01:00:25,204 --> 01:00:27,205\r\nPart that counts, anyway.\r\n\r\n853\r\n01:00:28,875 --> 01:00:31,501\r\n[JAKE CROWING]\r\n\r\n854\r\n01:00:34,797 --> 01:00:37,716\r\nI can't take care of you no more, Jake.\r\n\r\n855\r\n01:00:38,885 --> 01:00:40,552\r\nYou go on now.\r\n\r\n856\r\n01:00:41,804 --> 01:00:46,141\r\nYou're free.\r\n\r\n857\r\n01:01:02,450 --> 01:01:04,993\r\nBye. Joe?\r\n\r\n858\r\n01:01:05,161 --> 01:01:06,828\r\nGUARD:\r\nGood luck, Brooksie.\r\n\r\n859\r\n01:01:09,123 --> 01:01:11,208\r\nTake care of yourself, Brooks.\r\n\r\n860\r\n01:01:44,784 --> 01:01:46,284\r\nBROOKS:\r\nDear fellas:\r\n\r\n861\r\n01:01:46,577 --> 01:01:50,789\r\nI can't believe how fast things move\r\non the outside.\r\n\r\n862\r\n01:01:52,083 --> 01:01:54,751\r\nMAN:\r\nWatch it, old-timer! Want to get killed?\r\n\r\n863\r\n01:01:55,962 --> 01:01:59,464\r\nBROOKS: I saw an automobile once\r\nwhen I was a kid...\r\n\r\n864\r\n01:02:00,133 --> 01:02:02,551\r\n...but now they're everywhere.\r\n\r\n865\r\n01:02:06,222 --> 01:02:10,517\r\nThe world went and got itself\r\nin a big damn hurry.\r\n\r\n866\r\n01:02:26,325 --> 01:02:30,120\r\nThe parole board\r\ngot me into this halfway house...\r\n\r\n867\r\n01:02:30,413 --> 01:02:32,080\r\n...called \"The Brewer\"...\r\n\r\n868\r\n01:02:32,290 --> 01:02:33,457\r\n...and a job...\r\n\r\n869\r\n01:02:33,666 --> 01:02:36,626\r\n...bagging groceries at the Food-Way.\r\n\r\n870\r\n01:02:38,171 --> 01:02:40,589\r\nIt's hard work and I try to keep up...\r\n\r\n871\r\n01:02:40,798 --> 01:02:43,175\r\n...but my hands hurt most of the time.\r\n\r\n872\r\n01:02:43,468 --> 01:02:48,346\r\nMake sure your man double-bags.\r\nLast time, the bottom near came out.\r\n\r\n873\r\n01:02:48,514 --> 01:02:51,266\r\nMake sure you double-bag\r\nlike the lady says. Understand?\r\n\r\n874\r\n01:02:51,476 --> 01:02:52,851\r\nYes, sir. Surely will.\r\n\r\n875\r\n01:02:53,019 --> 01:02:56,563\r\nBROOKS: I don't think the store manager\r\nlikes me very much.\r\n\r\n876\r\n01:02:59,567 --> 01:03:03,862\r\nSometimes after work,\r\nI go to the park and feed the birds.\r\n\r\n877\r\n01:03:04,322 --> 01:03:05,822\r\nI keep thinking...\r\n\r\n878\r\n01:03:06,032 --> 01:03:09,367\r\n...Jake might just show up\r\nand say hello.\r\n\r\n879\r\n01:03:09,994 --> 01:03:11,995\r\nBut he never does.\r\n\r\n880\r\n01:03:13,206 --> 01:03:18,043\r\nI hope, wherever he is, he's doing okay\r\nand making new friends.\r\n\r\n881\r\n01:03:21,672 --> 01:03:24,382\r\nI have trouble sleeping at night.\r\n\r\n882\r\n01:03:24,717 --> 01:03:27,969\r\nI have bad dreams, like I'm falling.\r\n\r\n883\r\n01:03:28,221 --> 01:03:30,472\r\nI wake up scared.\r\n\r\n884\r\n01:03:30,681 --> 01:03:34,893\r\nSometimes it takes me a while\r\nto remember where I am.\r\n\r\n885\r\n01:03:36,395 --> 01:03:41,316\r\nMaybe I should get me a gun and rob\r\nthe Food-Way so they'd send me home.\r\n\r\n886\r\n01:03:41,609 --> 01:03:45,946\r\nI could shoot the manager while\r\nI was at it. Sort of like a bonus.\r\n\r\n887\r\n01:03:47,615 --> 01:03:51,618\r\nI guess I'm too old\r\nfor that sort of nonsense anymore.\r\n\r\n888\r\n01:03:51,869 --> 01:03:53,578\r\nI don't like it here.\r\n\r\n889\r\n01:03:53,788 --> 01:03:57,791\r\nI'm tired of being afraid all the time.\r\nI've decided...\r\n\r\n890\r\n01:03:58,626 --> 01:04:00,293\r\n...not to stay.\r\n\r\n891\r\n01:04:11,222 --> 01:04:13,765\r\nI doubt they'll kick up any fuss...\r\n\r\n892\r\n01:04:13,975 --> 01:04:17,477\r\n...not for an old crook like me.\r\n\r\n893\r\n01:05:19,957 --> 01:05:24,210\r\nANDY: \"I doubt they'll kick up any fuss,\r\nnot for an old crook like me.\r\n\r\n894\r\n01:05:25,254 --> 01:05:29,090\r\nP.S. Tell Heywood I'm sorry\r\nI put a knife to his throat.\r\n\r\n895\r\n01:05:29,300 --> 01:05:31,635\r\nNo hard feelings. Brooks.\"\r\n\r\n896\r\n01:05:42,104 --> 01:05:44,064\r\nHe should have died in here.\r\n\r\n897\r\n01:05:49,612 --> 01:05:51,029\r\nHADLEY:\r\nWhat the fuck have you done?\r\n\r\n898\r\n01:05:51,197 --> 01:05:53,865\r\nIt's a goddamn mess,\r\nI'll tell you that.\r\n\r\n899\r\n01:05:59,413 --> 01:06:03,166\r\n- What's all this?\r\n- You tell me. They're addressed to you.\r\n\r\n900\r\n01:06:04,418 --> 01:06:05,752\r\nTake it.\r\n\r\n901\r\n01:06:14,303 --> 01:06:15,804\r\n\"Dear Mr. Dufresne:\r\n\r\n902\r\n01:06:16,931 --> 01:06:18,890\r\nIn response to your repeated inquiries...\r\n\r\n903\r\n01:06:19,100 --> 01:06:23,395\r\n...the state has allocated the enclosed\r\nfunds for your library project.\"\r\n\r\n904\r\n01:06:24,146 --> 01:06:25,981\r\nThis is $200.\r\n\r\n905\r\n01:06:26,190 --> 01:06:30,193\r\n\"In addition, the library district\r\nhas generously responded...\r\n\r\n906\r\n01:06:30,403 --> 01:06:32,946\r\n...with a donation of used books\r\nand sundries.\r\n\r\n907\r\n01:06:33,155 --> 01:06:37,283\r\nWe trust this will fill your needs.\r\nWe now consider the matter closed.\r\n\r\n908\r\n01:06:37,493 --> 01:06:39,369\r\nPlease stop sending us letters.\"\r\n\r\n909\r\n01:06:39,537 --> 01:06:42,205\r\nI want all this cleared out\r\nbefore the warden gets back.\r\n\r\n910\r\n01:06:42,415 --> 01:06:43,581\r\nYes, sir.\r\n\r\n911\r\n01:06:47,878 --> 01:06:49,045\r\nGood for you, Andy.\r\n\r\n912\r\n01:06:51,841 --> 01:06:53,258\r\nWow.\r\n\r\n913\r\n01:06:54,343 --> 01:06:56,261\r\nIt only took six years.\r\n\r\n914\r\n01:06:57,847 --> 01:07:00,598\r\nFrom now on, I'll write two\r\nletters a week instead of one.\r\n\r\n915\r\n01:07:00,766 --> 01:07:04,102\r\nI believe you're crazy enough.\r\nGet this stuff out...\r\n\r\n916\r\n01:07:04,395 --> 01:07:06,813\r\n...like he said.\r\nI've got to pinch a loaf.\r\n\r\n917\r\n01:07:07,023 --> 01:07:08,481\r\nWhen I come back...\r\n\r\n918\r\n01:07:08,691 --> 01:07:10,442\r\n...this is all gone, all right?\r\n\r\n919\r\n01:07:46,645 --> 01:07:50,440\r\n[ARIA FROM \"THE MARRIAGE OF FIGARO\"\r\nPLAYS ON RECORD PLAYER]\r\n\r\n920\r\n01:07:59,200 --> 01:08:00,617\r\nDo you hear that?\r\n\r\n921\r\n01:08:33,275 --> 01:08:36,528\r\n[SCREECHING]\r\n\r\n922\r\n01:09:08,435 --> 01:09:09,435\r\n[KNOCKING]\r\n\r\n923\r\n01:09:09,603 --> 01:09:12,814\r\nGUARD:\r\nDufresne! Dufresne!\r\n\r\n924\r\n01:09:13,065 --> 01:09:14,566\r\nAndy, let me out!\r\n\r\n925\r\n01:09:21,448 --> 01:09:26,411\r\nRED: I have no idea to this day what those\r\ntwo Italian ladies were singing about.\r\n\r\n926\r\n01:09:26,704 --> 01:09:28,913\r\nTruth is, I don't want to know.\r\n\r\n927\r\n01:09:29,123 --> 01:09:31,624\r\nSome things are best left unsaid.\r\n\r\n928\r\n01:09:35,212 --> 01:09:37,922\r\nI like to think it was something\r\nso beautiful...\r\n\r\n929\r\n01:09:38,132 --> 01:09:40,258\r\n...it can't be expressed in words...\r\n\r\n930\r\n01:09:40,467 --> 01:09:43,386\r\n...and makes your heart ache\r\nbecause of it.\r\n\r\n931\r\n01:09:45,055 --> 01:09:47,557\r\nI tell you, those voices soared...\r\n\r\n932\r\n01:09:47,808 --> 01:09:52,103\r\n...higher and farther than anybody\r\nin a gray place dares to dream.\r\n\r\n933\r\n01:09:52,313 --> 01:09:55,690\r\nIt was like a beautiful bird\r\nflapped into our drab cage...\r\n\r\n934\r\n01:09:55,900 --> 01:09:58,651\r\n...and made those walls dissolve away.\r\n\r\n935\r\n01:09:59,111 --> 01:10:01,279\r\nAnd for the briefest of moments...\r\n\r\n936\r\n01:10:01,488 --> 01:10:04,490\r\n...every last man at Shawshank felt free.\r\n\r\n937\r\n01:10:07,077 --> 01:10:09,746\r\nIt pissed the warden off\r\nsomething awful.\r\n\r\n938\r\n01:10:11,040 --> 01:10:12,040\r\nOpen the door.\r\n\r\n939\r\n01:10:14,960 --> 01:10:16,711\r\nOpen it up!\r\n\r\n940\r\n01:10:18,005 --> 01:10:20,757\r\nDufresne, open this door!\r\n\r\n941\r\n01:10:22,092 --> 01:10:23,301\r\nTurn that off!\r\n\r\n942\r\n01:10:30,351 --> 01:10:32,810\r\nI am warning you. Turn that off!\r\n\r\n943\r\n01:10:46,659 --> 01:10:48,576\r\nDufresne.\r\n\r\n944\r\n01:10:50,537 --> 01:10:52,080\r\nYou're mine now.\r\n\r\n945\r\n01:10:59,505 --> 01:11:02,757\r\nRED: Andy got two weeks in the hole\r\nfor that little stunt.\r\n\r\n946\r\n01:11:02,967 --> 01:11:04,550\r\nHADLEY:\r\nOn your feet.\r\n\r\n947\r\n01:11:05,719 --> 01:11:08,137\r\nJIGGER: Hey, look who's here.\r\nSNOOZE: Maestro!\r\n\r\n948\r\n01:11:08,305 --> 01:11:09,514\r\nHey.\r\n\r\n949\r\n01:11:09,890 --> 01:11:13,559\r\nYou couldn't play something good, huh?\r\nLike Hank Williams?\r\n\r\n950\r\n01:11:13,894 --> 01:11:16,688\r\nThey broke the door down\r\nbefore I could take requests.\r\n\r\n951\r\n01:11:16,897 --> 01:11:20,024\r\n- Was it worth two weeks?\r\n- Easiest time I ever did.\r\n\r\n952\r\n01:11:20,234 --> 01:11:22,568\r\nNo such thing as easy time in the hole.\r\n\r\n953\r\n01:11:22,736 --> 01:11:24,445\r\nJIGGER:\r\nA week in the hole is like a year.\r\n\r\n954\r\n01:11:24,655 --> 01:11:27,949\r\nSNOOZE: Damn straight.\r\n- I had Mr. Mozart to keep me company.\r\n\r\n955\r\n01:11:28,158 --> 01:11:31,119\r\nSo they let you tote\r\nthat record player down there, huh?\r\n\r\n956\r\n01:11:33,539 --> 01:11:34,914\r\nIt was in here.\r\n\r\n957\r\n01:11:35,749 --> 01:11:37,000\r\nIn here.\r\n\r\n958\r\n01:11:38,127 --> 01:11:40,211\r\nThat's the beauty of music. They...\r\n\r\n959\r\n01:11:40,421 --> 01:11:42,755\r\n...can't get that from you.\r\n\r\n960\r\n01:11:46,302 --> 01:11:48,678\r\nHaven't you ever felt\r\nthat way about music?\r\n\r\n961\r\n01:11:50,472 --> 01:11:53,599\r\nWell, I played a mean harmonica\r\nas a younger man.\r\n\r\n962\r\n01:11:54,643 --> 01:11:56,352\r\nLost interest in it, though.\r\n\r\n963\r\n01:11:56,562 --> 01:11:58,146\r\nDidn't make much sense in here.\r\n\r\n964\r\n01:11:58,480 --> 01:12:00,481\r\nANDY:\r\nHere's where it makes the most sense.\r\n\r\n965\r\n01:12:01,025 --> 01:12:03,067\r\nYou need it so you don't forget.\r\n\r\n966\r\n01:12:03,652 --> 01:12:04,944\r\nForget?\r\n\r\n967\r\n01:12:05,237 --> 01:12:08,323\r\nForget that there are...\r\n\r\n968\r\n01:12:08,532 --> 01:12:09,949\r\n...places...\r\n\r\n969\r\n01:12:10,451 --> 01:12:14,287\r\n...in the world\r\nthat aren't made out of stone.\r\n\r\n970\r\n01:12:15,289 --> 01:12:16,789\r\nThere's something...\r\n\r\n971\r\n01:12:17,124 --> 01:12:18,541\r\n...inside...\r\n\r\n972\r\n01:12:18,792 --> 01:12:20,752\r\n...that they can't get to...\r\n\r\n973\r\n01:12:20,961 --> 01:12:22,378\r\n...that they can't touch.\r\n\r\n974\r\n01:12:22,880 --> 01:12:24,297\r\nThat's yours.\r\n\r\n975\r\n01:12:25,841 --> 01:12:27,425\r\nWhat are you talking about?\r\n\r\n976\r\n01:12:28,469 --> 01:12:32,096\r\nHope.\r\n\r\n977\r\n01:12:34,058 --> 01:12:36,059\r\nLet me tell you something, my friend.\r\n\r\n978\r\n01:12:36,852 --> 01:12:39,145\r\nHope is a dangerous thing.\r\n\r\n979\r\n01:12:40,314 --> 01:12:42,648\r\nHope can drive a man insane.\r\n\r\n980\r\n01:12:43,400 --> 01:12:45,526\r\nIt's got no use on the inside.\r\n\r\n981\r\n01:12:45,736 --> 01:12:47,945\r\nYou'd better get used to that idea.\r\n\r\n982\r\n01:12:50,449 --> 01:12:51,949\r\nLike Brooks did?\r\n\r\n983\r\n01:13:17,309 --> 01:13:18,309\r\nSit down.\r\n\r\n984\r\n01:13:23,649 --> 01:13:26,943\r\nSays here that you've served\r\n30 years of a life sentence.\r\n\r\n985\r\n01:13:28,112 --> 01:13:30,154\r\nYou feel you've been rehabilitated?\r\n\r\n986\r\n01:13:30,364 --> 01:13:31,614\r\nOh, yes, sir.\r\n\r\n987\r\n01:13:32,866 --> 01:13:34,200\r\nWithout a doubt.\r\n\r\n988\r\n01:13:35,369 --> 01:13:37,787\r\nI can honestly say I'm a changed man.\r\n\r\n989\r\n01:13:39,790 --> 01:13:41,707\r\nNo danger to society here.\r\n\r\n990\r\n01:13:42,251 --> 01:13:43,793\r\nGod's honest truth.\r\n\r\n991\r\n01:13:46,338 --> 01:13:48,464\r\nAbsolutely rehabilitated.\r\n\r\n992\r\n01:13:58,434 --> 01:13:59,767\r\nThirty years.\r\n\r\n993\r\n01:14:01,728 --> 01:14:03,646\r\nJesus, when you say it like that...\r\n\r\n994\r\n01:14:04,523 --> 01:14:06,315\r\nYou wonder where it went.\r\n\r\n995\r\n01:14:08,735 --> 01:14:10,903\r\nI wonder where 10 years went.\r\n\r\n996\r\n01:14:15,868 --> 01:14:16,909\r\nHere.\r\n\r\n997\r\n01:14:17,369 --> 01:14:20,079\r\nA little parole-rejection present.\r\n\r\n998\r\n01:14:21,373 --> 01:14:23,040\r\nGo ahead and open it.\r\n\r\n999\r\n01:14:24,168 --> 01:14:26,210\r\nWent through one of your competitors.\r\n\r\n1000\r\n01:14:26,378 --> 01:14:29,547\r\nI hope you don't mind.\r\nI wanted it to be a surprise.\r\n\r\n1001\r\n01:14:39,558 --> 01:14:41,058\r\nIt's very pretty.\r\n\r\n1002\r\n01:14:42,769 --> 01:14:43,978\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n1003\r\n01:14:46,565 --> 01:14:48,024\r\nYou going to play it?\r\n\r\n1004\r\n01:14:52,571 --> 01:14:53,863\r\nNo.\r\n\r\n1005\r\n01:14:57,451 --> 01:14:58,868\r\nNot right now.\r\n\r\n1006\r\n01:15:04,750 --> 01:15:07,835\r\n[GUARDS SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]\r\n\r\n1007\r\n01:15:16,553 --> 01:15:17,637\r\nGUARD:\r\nRoll in!\r\n\r\n1008\r\n01:15:53,840 --> 01:15:55,091\r\nGUARD:\r\nLights out!\r\n\r\n1009\r\n01:16:29,668 --> 01:16:31,836\r\nRED:\r\nAndy was as good as his word.\r\n\r\n1010\r\n01:16:32,170 --> 01:16:34,964\r\nHe wrote two letters a week\r\ninstead of one.\r\n\r\n1011\r\n01:16:37,009 --> 01:16:41,137\r\nIn 1959, the state senate\r\nfinally clued in to the fact...\r\n\r\n1012\r\n01:16:41,346 --> 01:16:44,515\r\n...they couldn't buy him off\r\nwith just a $200 check.\r\n\r\n1013\r\n01:16:44,683 --> 01:16:49,020\r\nAppropriations Committee\r\nvoted an annual payment of $500...\r\n\r\n1014\r\n01:16:49,187 --> 01:16:51,105\r\n...just to shut him up.\r\n\r\n1015\r\n01:16:51,315 --> 01:16:54,317\r\nAnd you'd be amazed how far\r\nAndy could stretch it.\r\n\r\n1016\r\n01:16:54,526 --> 01:16:57,445\r\nHe made deals with book clubs,\r\ncharity groups.\r\n\r\n1017\r\n01:16:57,654 --> 01:17:00,406\r\nHe bought remaindered books\r\nby the pound...\r\n\r\n1018\r\n01:17:00,907 --> 01:17:02,450\r\n\"Treasure Island.\"\r\n\r\n1019\r\n01:17:02,993 --> 01:17:04,327\r\nRobert Louis...\r\n\r\n1020\r\n01:17:04,536 --> 01:17:05,536\r\nStevenson.\r\n\r\n1021\r\n01:17:05,746 --> 01:17:07,163\r\nFiction, adventure.\r\n\r\n1022\r\n01:17:09,708 --> 01:17:10,750\r\nWhat's next?\r\n\r\n1023\r\n01:17:10,917 --> 01:17:14,003\r\nI got here Auto Repair...\r\n\r\n1024\r\n01:17:14,713 --> 01:17:15,880\r\n...and Soap Carving.\r\n\r\n1025\r\n01:17:16,089 --> 01:17:19,342\r\nTrade skills and hobbies.\r\nUnder \"Educational,\" behind you.\r\n\r\n1026\r\n01:17:19,551 --> 01:17:21,385\r\n\"Count of Monte Crisco.\"\r\n\r\n1027\r\n01:17:21,887 --> 01:17:24,180\r\nThat's \"Cristo,\" you dumb-shit.\r\n\r\n1028\r\n01:17:25,265 --> 01:17:26,265\r\nBy Alexandree...\r\n\r\n1029\r\n01:17:26,725 --> 01:17:28,017\r\n...Dum-ass.\r\n\r\n1030\r\n01:17:28,352 --> 01:17:29,393\r\nDumb-ass.\r\n\r\n1031\r\n01:17:31,688 --> 01:17:32,730\r\nDumb-ass?\r\n\r\n1032\r\n01:17:35,651 --> 01:17:38,944\r\n- Dumas. Know what that's about?\r\n- Huh.\r\n\r\n1033\r\n01:17:39,905 --> 01:17:41,906\r\nYou'd like it. It's about a prison break.\r\n\r\n1034\r\n01:17:42,074 --> 01:17:45,951\r\nWe ought to file that\r\nunder \"Educational\" too, oughtn't we?\r\n\r\n1035\r\n01:17:46,828 --> 01:17:50,915\r\nRED: The rest of us did our best\r\nto pitch in when and where we could.\r\n\r\n1036\r\n01:17:51,500 --> 01:17:53,250\r\nBy the year Kennedy was shot...\r\n\r\n1037\r\n01:17:53,502 --> 01:17:58,005\r\n...Andy had transformed a storage room\r\nsmelling of turpentine...\r\n\r\n1038\r\n01:17:58,298 --> 01:18:01,425\r\n...into the best prison library\r\nin New England...\r\n\r\n1039\r\n01:18:02,094 --> 01:18:05,054\r\n...complete with a fine selection\r\nof Hank Williams.\r\n\r\n1040\r\n01:18:05,222 --> 01:18:08,766\r\n[SINGING HANK WILLIAMS'\r\n\"LOVE SICK BLUES\"]\r\n\r\n1041\r\n01:18:12,437 --> 01:18:14,355\r\nThat was also when Warden Norton...\r\n\r\n1042\r\n01:18:14,564 --> 01:18:17,483\r\n...instituted his famous\r\n\"Inside Out\" program.\r\n\r\n1043\r\n01:18:17,943 --> 01:18:20,027\r\nYou may remember reading about it.\r\n\r\n1044\r\n01:18:20,278 --> 01:18:23,364\r\nIt made the papers\r\nand got his picture in Look magazine.\r\n\r\n1045\r\n01:18:23,573 --> 01:18:24,907\r\nIt's no free ride...\r\n\r\n1046\r\n01:18:25,075 --> 01:18:28,285\r\n...but rather a genuine\r\nprogressive advance...\r\n\r\n1047\r\n01:18:28,495 --> 01:18:30,996\r\n...in corrections and rehabilitation.\r\n\r\n1048\r\n01:18:31,331 --> 01:18:33,874\r\nOur inmates, properly supervised...\r\n\r\n1049\r\n01:18:34,084 --> 01:18:36,711\r\n...will be put to work\r\noutside these walls...\r\n\r\n1050\r\n01:18:36,920 --> 01:18:40,005\r\n...performing all manner\r\nof public service.\r\n\r\n1051\r\n01:18:40,173 --> 01:18:42,967\r\nThese men can learn the value\r\nof an honest day's labor...\r\n\r\n1052\r\n01:18:43,176 --> 01:18:46,971\r\n...while providing a valuable service\r\nto the community...\r\n\r\n1053\r\n01:18:47,180 --> 01:18:51,892\r\n...and at a bare minimum of expense\r\nto Mr. And Mrs. John Q. Taxpayer.\r\n\r\n1054\r\n01:18:52,310 --> 01:18:54,645\r\nRED:\r\nOf course he didn't tell the press...\r\n\r\n1055\r\n01:18:54,855 --> 01:18:58,315\r\n...that \"bare minimum of expense\"\r\nis a fairly loose term.\r\n\r\n1056\r\n01:18:58,525 --> 01:19:01,569\r\nThere are 100 different ways\r\nto skim off the top.\r\n\r\n1057\r\n01:19:01,778 --> 01:19:04,280\r\nMen, materials, you name it.\r\n\r\n1058\r\n01:19:04,614 --> 01:19:07,491\r\nAnd oh, my Lord,\r\nhow the money rolled in!\r\n\r\n1059\r\n01:19:07,701 --> 01:19:10,244\r\n- You'll put me out of business.\r\n- Ned.\r\n\r\n1060\r\n01:19:10,454 --> 01:19:14,874\r\nWith this pool of slave labor,\r\nyou can underbid any contractor in town.\r\n\r\n1061\r\n01:19:15,459 --> 01:19:18,419\r\nWe're providing\r\na valuable community service.\r\n\r\n1062\r\n01:19:18,628 --> 01:19:23,966\r\nThat's fine for the papers,\r\nbut I've got a family to feed. Sam.\r\n\r\n1063\r\n01:19:24,968 --> 01:19:26,510\r\nWe go back a long way, Sam.\r\n\r\n1064\r\n01:19:27,804 --> 01:19:32,725\r\nI need this new highway contract.\r\nI don't get it and I go under. That's a fact.\r\n\r\n1065\r\n01:19:33,643 --> 01:19:35,436\r\nYou have some of this fine pie...\r\n\r\n1066\r\n01:19:35,687 --> 01:19:39,023\r\n...my missus made especially for you.\r\nYou think about that.\r\n\r\n1067\r\n01:19:47,282 --> 01:19:49,992\r\nNed, I wouldn't worry too much\r\nabout this contract.\r\n\r\n1068\r\n01:19:50,202 --> 01:19:53,287\r\nIt seems to me I already got my boys\r\ncommitted elsewhere.\r\n\r\n1069\r\n01:19:55,248 --> 01:19:58,334\r\nYou be sure and thank Maisie\r\nfor this fine pie.\r\n\r\n1070\r\n01:19:59,419 --> 01:20:01,587\r\nRED:\r\nAnd behind every shady deal...\r\n\r\n1071\r\n01:20:01,922 --> 01:20:04,548\r\n...behind every dollar earned...\r\n\r\n1072\r\n01:20:04,841 --> 01:20:07,885\r\n...there was Andy, keeping the books.\r\n\r\n1073\r\n01:20:08,303 --> 01:20:09,553\r\nTwo deposits.\r\n\r\n1074\r\n01:20:09,805 --> 01:20:13,933\r\nMaine National and New England First.\r\nNight drops as always, sir.\r\n\r\n1075\r\n01:20:44,130 --> 01:20:48,467\r\nGet my stuff to the laundry. Two suits\r\nfor dry-clean and a bag of whatnot.\r\n\r\n1076\r\n01:20:48,927 --> 01:20:51,846\r\nIf they over-starch my shirts again,\r\nthey'll hear from me.\r\n\r\n1077\r\n01:20:52,013 --> 01:20:54,014\r\n- Yes, sir.\r\n- How do I look?\r\n\r\n1078\r\n01:20:55,058 --> 01:20:57,560\r\n- Very nice.\r\n- Big charity to-do up Portland way.\r\n\r\n1079\r\n01:20:57,769 --> 01:20:59,270\r\n- Governor will be there.\r\n- Hmm.\r\n\r\n1080\r\n01:21:00,689 --> 01:21:02,147\r\nYou want the rest of this?\r\n\r\n1081\r\n01:21:03,483 --> 01:21:05,442\r\nWoman can't bake worth shit.\r\n\r\n1082\r\n01:21:06,653 --> 01:21:07,987\r\nThank you, sir.\r\n\r\n1083\r\n01:21:10,824 --> 01:21:14,076\r\nHe's got his fingers\r\nin a lot of pies, from what I hear.\r\n\r\n1084\r\n01:21:14,286 --> 01:21:19,123\r\nHe's got scams you haven't even\r\ndreamed of. Kickbacks on his kickbacks.\r\n\r\n1085\r\n01:21:19,291 --> 01:21:21,667\r\nA river of dirty money\r\nrunning through here.\r\n\r\n1086\r\n01:21:21,877 --> 01:21:25,713\r\nSooner or later, he'll have to\r\nexplain where it came from.\r\n\r\n1087\r\n01:21:25,922 --> 01:21:27,673\r\nThat's where I come in.\r\n\r\n1088\r\n01:21:28,300 --> 01:21:30,593\r\nI channel it. Filter it. Funnel it.\r\n\r\n1089\r\n01:21:30,802 --> 01:21:33,637\r\nStocks, securities,\r\ntax-free municipals.\r\n\r\n1090\r\n01:21:33,972 --> 01:21:37,474\r\nI send it out into the real world,\r\nand when it comes back...\r\n\r\n1091\r\n01:21:37,684 --> 01:21:40,644\r\n- Clean as a virgin's honeypot, huh?\r\n- Cleaner.\r\n\r\n1092\r\n01:21:41,271 --> 01:21:44,857\r\nBy the time Norton retires,\r\nI'll have made him a millionaire.\r\n\r\n1093\r\n01:21:47,193 --> 01:21:51,530\r\nIf they ever catch on, he'll wind up\r\nin here wearing a number himself.\r\n\r\n1094\r\n01:21:51,823 --> 01:21:54,491\r\nI thought you had\r\nmore faith in me than that.\r\n\r\n1095\r\n01:21:54,701 --> 01:21:57,745\r\nI know you're good,\r\nbut all that paper leaves a trail.\r\n\r\n1096\r\n01:21:58,121 --> 01:21:59,955\r\nNow anybody gets curious...\r\n\r\n1097\r\n01:22:00,123 --> 01:22:02,541\r\nFBI, IRS, whatever.\r\n\r\n1098\r\n01:22:03,001 --> 01:22:04,293\r\n- It'll lead to somebody.\r\n\r\n1099\r\n01:22:04,502 --> 01:22:08,339\r\nSure it is, but not to me,\r\nand certainly not to the warden.\r\n\r\n1100\r\n01:22:12,719 --> 01:22:13,719\r\nAll right, who?\r\n\r\n1101\r\n01:22:13,887 --> 01:22:15,512\r\nRandall Stevens.\r\n\r\n1102\r\n01:22:16,014 --> 01:22:17,014\r\nWho?\r\n\r\n1103\r\n01:22:17,182 --> 01:22:19,183\r\nThe \"silent\" silent partner.\r\n\r\n1104\r\n01:22:19,392 --> 01:22:22,478\r\nHe's the guilty one,\r\nthe man with the bank accounts.\r\n\r\n1105\r\n01:22:22,687 --> 01:22:24,855\r\nIt's where the filtering\r\nprocess starts.\r\n\r\n1106\r\n01:22:25,023 --> 01:22:27,900\r\nThey trace anything,\r\nit'll just lead to him.\r\n\r\n1107\r\n01:22:28,526 --> 01:22:29,735\r\nBut who is he?\r\n\r\n1108\r\n01:22:29,945 --> 01:22:33,906\r\nHe's a phantom, an apparition.\r\nSecond cousin to Harvey the Rabbit.\r\n\r\n1109\r\n01:22:35,033 --> 01:22:36,200\r\nI conjured him...\r\n\r\n1110\r\n01:22:36,368 --> 01:22:37,743\r\n...out of thin air.\r\n\r\n1111\r\n01:22:38,536 --> 01:22:41,288\r\nHe doesn't exist, except on paper.\r\n\r\n1112\r\n01:22:44,376 --> 01:22:46,710\r\nAndy, you can't just make a person up.\r\n\r\n1113\r\n01:22:46,920 --> 01:22:50,047\r\nSure you can,\r\nif you know how the system works.\r\n\r\n1114\r\n01:22:50,548 --> 01:22:53,384\r\nIt's amazing what you\r\ncan accomplish by mail.\r\n\r\n1115\r\n01:22:53,718 --> 01:22:56,345\r\nMr. Stevens has a birth certificate...\r\n\r\n1116\r\n01:22:56,554 --> 01:22:58,681\r\n...driver's license, Social Security number.\r\n\r\n1117\r\n01:22:58,932 --> 01:22:59,932\r\nYou're shitting me.\r\n\r\n1118\r\n01:23:00,100 --> 01:23:03,519\r\nIf they trace any accounts,\r\nthey'll wind up chasing...\r\n\r\n1119\r\n01:23:03,728 --> 01:23:05,437\r\n...a figment of my imagination.\r\n\r\n1120\r\n01:23:05,647 --> 01:23:07,648\r\nWell, I'll be damned!\r\n\r\n1121\r\n01:23:08,984 --> 01:23:10,734\r\nDid I say you were good?\r\n\r\n1122\r\n01:23:11,069 --> 01:23:12,736\r\nShit, you are Rembrandt.\r\n\r\n1123\r\n01:23:13,446 --> 01:23:15,197\r\nThe funny thing is...\r\n\r\n1124\r\n01:23:15,407 --> 01:23:19,493\r\n...on the outside, I was an honest man,\r\nstraight as an arrow.\r\n\r\n1125\r\n01:23:19,911 --> 01:23:22,246\r\nI had to come to prison to be a crook.\r\n\r\n1126\r\n01:23:23,206 --> 01:23:26,458\r\n[CHUCKLING]\r\n\r\n1127\r\n01:23:31,089 --> 01:23:32,423\r\nEver bother you?\r\n\r\n1128\r\n01:23:33,842 --> 01:23:36,927\r\nI don't run the scams.\r\nI just process the profits.\r\n\r\n1129\r\n01:23:37,178 --> 01:23:39,179\r\nA fine line, maybe...\r\n\r\n1130\r\n01:23:39,764 --> 01:23:41,807\r\n...but I also built that library...\r\n\r\n1131\r\n01:23:42,017 --> 01:23:45,060\r\n...and used it to help guys\r\nget their high school diploma.\r\n\r\n1132\r\n01:23:45,270 --> 01:23:47,479\r\nWhy do you think\r\nhe lets me do all that?\r\n\r\n1133\r\n01:23:47,689 --> 01:23:49,898\r\nKeep you happy and doing the laundry.\r\n\r\n1134\r\n01:23:50,108 --> 01:23:51,567\r\nMoney instead of sheets.\r\n\r\n1135\r\n01:23:51,943 --> 01:23:54,486\r\nWell, I work cheap.\r\nThat's the tradeoff.\r\n\r\n1136\r\n01:23:54,654 --> 01:23:57,990\r\n[SIREN WAILING]\r\n\r\n1137\r\n01:24:11,796 --> 01:24:14,423\r\nRED: Tommy Williams came\r\nto Shawshank in 1965...\r\n\r\n1138\r\n01:24:14,632 --> 01:24:16,884\r\n...on a two-year stretch for B and E.\r\n\r\n1139\r\n01:24:17,135 --> 01:24:19,470\r\nThat's breaking and entering to you.\r\n\r\n1140\r\n01:24:19,721 --> 01:24:23,974\r\nCops caught him sneaking TV sets\r\nout the back door of a JC Penney.\r\n\r\n1141\r\n01:24:24,392 --> 01:24:25,684\r\nYoung punk.\r\n\r\n1142\r\n01:24:25,894 --> 01:24:27,519\r\nMr. Rock 'n' Roll...\r\n\r\n1143\r\n01:24:27,729 --> 01:24:29,271\r\n...cocky as hell.\r\n\r\n1144\r\n01:24:29,481 --> 01:24:31,857\r\nCome on, old boys.\r\nMoving like molasses!\r\n\r\n1145\r\n01:24:32,108 --> 01:24:33,859\r\nMaking me look bad.\r\n\r\n1146\r\n01:24:34,069 --> 01:24:35,861\r\nRED:\r\nWe liked him immediately.\r\n\r\n1147\r\n01:24:36,112 --> 01:24:39,823\r\nI'm backing out the door\r\nand I got the TV like this.\r\n\r\n1148\r\n01:24:40,158 --> 01:24:43,786\r\nA big old thing. I couldn't see shit.\r\nThen I hear this voice.\r\n\r\n1149\r\n01:24:44,412 --> 01:24:46,371\r\n\"Freeze, kid, hands in the air.\"\r\n\r\n1150\r\n01:24:46,581 --> 01:24:51,043\r\nI was standing there, holding onto\r\nthat TV. Finally the voice says:\r\n\r\n1151\r\n01:24:51,252 --> 01:24:55,047\r\n\"You hear what I said, boy?\"\r\nI say, \"Yes, sir. I sure did.\r\n\r\n1152\r\n01:24:55,256 --> 01:24:58,717\r\nBut if I drop this, you get me\r\non destruction of property too.\"\r\n\r\n1153\r\n01:24:58,927 --> 01:25:01,386\r\n[LAUGHING]\r\n\r\n1154\r\n01:25:03,181 --> 01:25:05,849\r\nHey, you done some stretch\r\nin Cashman, right?\r\n\r\n1155\r\n01:25:06,017 --> 01:25:09,978\r\nYeah, that was an easy piece of time,\r\nlet me tell you.\r\n\r\n1156\r\n01:25:10,230 --> 01:25:12,189\r\nWeekend furloughs. Work programs.\r\n\r\n1157\r\n01:25:12,857 --> 01:25:14,149\r\nNot like here.\r\n\r\n1158\r\n01:25:14,317 --> 01:25:16,068\r\nSounds like you done time all over.\r\n\r\n1159\r\n01:25:16,528 --> 01:25:18,904\r\nYeah, I've been in and out since I was 13.\r\n\r\n1160\r\n01:25:19,114 --> 01:25:21,323\r\nYou name it, chances are I've been there.\r\n\r\n1161\r\n01:25:21,533 --> 01:25:24,201\r\nPerhaps you should try a new profession.\r\n\r\n1162\r\n01:25:25,620 --> 01:25:27,204\r\nWhat I mean is...\r\n\r\n1163\r\n01:25:27,539 --> 01:25:30,499\r\n...you're not a very good thief.\r\nYou should try something else.\r\n\r\n1164\r\n01:25:31,209 --> 01:25:34,419\r\nYeah, what the hell\r\nyou know about it, Capone?\r\n\r\n1165\r\n01:25:34,838 --> 01:25:36,421\r\nWhat are you in for?\r\n\r\n1166\r\n01:25:36,714 --> 01:25:37,714\r\nMe?\r\n\r\n1167\r\n01:25:40,135 --> 01:25:41,802\r\nA lawyer fucked me.\r\n\r\n1168\r\n01:25:45,723 --> 01:25:48,684\r\nEverybody's innocent in here.\r\nDon't you know that?\r\n\r\n1169\r\n01:25:56,568 --> 01:26:00,988\r\nRED: As it turned out, Tommy had himself\r\na young wife and a new baby girl.\r\n\r\n1170\r\n01:26:01,573 --> 01:26:03,699\r\nMaybe he thought of them\r\non the streets...\r\n\r\n1171\r\n01:26:03,908 --> 01:26:06,410\r\n...or his child growing up\r\nnot knowing her daddy.\r\n\r\n1172\r\n01:26:06,703 --> 01:26:08,078\r\nWhatever it was...\r\n\r\n1173\r\n01:26:08,413 --> 01:26:10,831\r\n...something lit a fire\r\nunder that boy's ass.\r\n\r\n1174\r\n01:26:14,669 --> 01:26:17,546\r\nThought I might try for\r\nmy high school equivalency.\r\n\r\n1175\r\n01:26:17,755 --> 01:26:20,257\r\nHear you helped\r\na couple of fellas with that.\r\n\r\n1176\r\n01:26:21,593 --> 01:26:23,844\r\nI don't waste time with losers, Tommy.\r\n\r\n1177\r\n01:26:25,263 --> 01:26:27,764\r\nI ain't no goddamn loser.\r\n\r\n1178\r\n01:26:29,475 --> 01:26:31,310\r\n- You mean that?\r\n- Yeah.\r\n\r\n1179\r\n01:26:32,979 --> 01:26:34,438\r\nYou really mean that?\r\n\r\n1180\r\n01:26:35,440 --> 01:26:36,815\r\nYes, sir, I do.\r\n\r\n1181\r\n01:26:37,025 --> 01:26:38,984\r\nGood. Because if we do this...\r\n\r\n1182\r\n01:26:39,194 --> 01:26:43,155\r\n...we do it all the way,\r\na hundred percent, nothing half-assed.\r\n\r\n1183\r\n01:26:43,406 --> 01:26:45,199\r\nThing is, see...\r\n\r\n1184\r\n01:26:46,451 --> 01:26:47,993\r\n...I don't read so good.\r\n\r\n1185\r\n01:26:49,162 --> 01:26:50,287\r\n\"Well.\"\r\n\r\n1186\r\n01:26:52,290 --> 01:26:53,999\r\nYou don't read...\r\n\r\n1187\r\n01:26:54,250 --> 01:26:55,792\r\n...so well.\r\n\r\n1188\r\n01:26:58,129 --> 01:26:59,630\r\nWe'll get to that.\r\n\r\n1189\r\n01:27:04,052 --> 01:27:06,178\r\nRED:\r\nSo Andy took Tommy under his wing.\r\n\r\n1190\r\n01:27:06,387 --> 01:27:09,014\r\nStarted walking him through his ABC's.\r\n\r\n1191\r\n01:27:11,142 --> 01:27:13,352\r\nTommy took to it pretty well too.\r\n\r\n1192\r\n01:27:13,645 --> 01:27:16,396\r\nBoy found brains he never knew he had.\r\n\r\n1193\r\n01:27:18,733 --> 01:27:22,152\r\nBefore long, Andy started him\r\non his course requirements.\r\n\r\n1194\r\n01:27:22,362 --> 01:27:24,029\r\nHe really liked the kid.\r\n\r\n1195\r\n01:27:24,239 --> 01:27:27,824\r\nGave him a thrill to help a youngster\r\ncrawl off the shit heap.\r\n\r\n1196\r\n01:27:28,326 --> 01:27:30,577\r\nBut that wasn't the only reason.\r\n\r\n1197\r\n01:27:31,287 --> 01:27:33,497\r\nPrison time is slow time.\r\n\r\n1198\r\n01:27:33,957 --> 01:27:36,541\r\nSo you do what you can to keep going.\r\n\r\n1199\r\n01:27:36,876 --> 01:27:38,961\r\nSome fellas collect stamps.\r\n\r\n1200\r\n01:27:39,337 --> 01:27:41,838\r\nOthers build matchstick houses.\r\n\r\n1201\r\n01:27:42,423 --> 01:27:45,092\r\nAndy built a library.\r\n\r\n1202\r\n01:27:45,593 --> 01:27:47,511\r\nNow he needed a new project.\r\n\r\n1203\r\n01:27:48,388 --> 01:27:49,888\r\nTommy was it.\r\n\r\n1204\r\n01:27:50,515 --> 01:27:54,518\r\nIt was the same reason he spent years\r\nshaping and polishing those rocks.\r\n\r\n1205\r\n01:27:55,061 --> 01:27:58,313\r\nThe same reason he hung\r\nhis fantasy girlies on the wall.\r\n\r\n1206\r\n01:27:59,190 --> 01:28:00,482\r\nIn prison...\r\n\r\n1207\r\n01:28:00,733 --> 01:28:04,486\r\n...a man will do most anything\r\nto keep his mind occupied.\r\n\r\n1208\r\n01:28:05,238 --> 01:28:10,117\r\nBy 1966, right about the time Tommy\r\nwas getting ready to take his exams...\r\n\r\n1209\r\n01:28:10,368 --> 01:28:12,536\r\n...it was lovely Raquel.\r\n\r\n1210\r\n01:28:13,079 --> 01:28:15,205\r\n[CLOCK TICKING]\r\n\r\n1211\r\n01:28:29,095 --> 01:28:30,095\r\nTime.\r\n\r\n1212\r\n01:28:36,144 --> 01:28:37,394\r\nWell?\r\n\r\n1213\r\n01:28:38,730 --> 01:28:40,897\r\nWell, it's for shit.\r\n\r\n1214\r\n01:28:41,399 --> 01:28:44,234\r\nI wasted a whole year\r\nof my time with this bullshit.\r\n\r\n1215\r\n01:28:44,402 --> 01:28:45,902\r\nIt's probably not that bad.\r\n\r\n1216\r\n01:28:46,112 --> 01:28:50,365\r\nYeah, I didn't get a thing right.\r\nIt might as well have been in Chinese.\r\n\r\n1217\r\n01:28:50,575 --> 01:28:52,284\r\nLet's see how the score comes out.\r\n\r\n1218\r\n01:28:52,493 --> 01:28:55,454\r\nYeah, well, I'll tell you\r\nhow the goddamn score comes out.\r\n\r\n1219\r\n01:28:57,415 --> 01:28:58,749\r\nTwo points, right there!\r\n\r\n1220\r\n01:28:58,958 --> 01:29:00,542\r\nThere's your goddamn score!\r\n\r\n1221\r\n01:29:00,752 --> 01:29:04,463\r\nGoddamn cats crawling up trees,\r\n5 times 5 is 25...\r\n\r\n1222\r\n01:29:05,423 --> 01:29:07,049\r\nFuck this place!\r\n\r\n1223\r\n01:29:07,258 --> 01:29:08,425\r\nFuck it!\r\n\r\n1224\r\n01:29:27,570 --> 01:29:28,820\r\nI feel bad.\r\n\r\n1225\r\n01:29:29,030 --> 01:29:30,238\r\nI let him down.\r\n\r\n1226\r\n01:29:30,448 --> 01:29:32,157\r\nThat's crap, kid.\r\n\r\n1227\r\n01:29:32,367 --> 01:29:33,700\r\nHe's proud of you.\r\n\r\n1228\r\n01:29:34,035 --> 01:29:36,912\r\nWe're old friends,\r\nI know him as good as anybody.\r\n\r\n1229\r\n01:29:37,121 --> 01:29:38,663\r\nSmart fellow, ain't he?\r\n\r\n1230\r\n01:29:38,873 --> 01:29:42,000\r\nSmart as they come.\r\nHe was a banker on the outside.\r\n\r\n1231\r\n01:29:42,210 --> 01:29:44,461\r\nWhat's he in here for anyway?\r\n\r\n1232\r\n01:29:44,754 --> 01:29:45,754\r\nMurder.\r\n\r\n1233\r\n01:29:47,215 --> 01:29:50,008\r\n- The hell, you say.\r\n- Hmm.\r\n\r\n1234\r\n01:29:50,718 --> 01:29:53,053\r\nYou wouldn't think it\r\nto look at the guy.\r\n\r\n1235\r\n01:29:54,305 --> 01:29:58,392\r\nCaught his wife in bed\r\nwith some golf pro. Greased them both.\r\n\r\n1236\r\n01:30:06,401 --> 01:30:07,776\r\nWhat?\r\n\r\n1237\r\n01:30:08,736 --> 01:30:11,321\r\nAbout four years ago...\r\n\r\n1238\r\n01:30:11,572 --> 01:30:14,825\r\n...I was in Thomaston\r\non a two-to-three stretch.\r\n\r\n1239\r\n01:30:15,326 --> 01:30:16,618\r\nI stole a car.\r\n\r\n1240\r\n01:30:16,994 --> 01:30:18,995\r\nIt was a dumb-fuck thing to do.\r\n\r\n1241\r\n01:30:19,664 --> 01:30:21,873\r\nAbout six months left to go...\r\n\r\n1242\r\n01:30:22,166 --> 01:30:24,084\r\n...I get a new cellmate in.\r\n\r\n1243\r\n01:30:24,794 --> 01:30:26,420\r\nElmo Blatch.\r\n\r\n1244\r\n01:30:27,130 --> 01:30:28,463\r\nBig, twitchy fucker.\r\n\r\n1245\r\n01:30:29,340 --> 01:30:32,843\r\nKind of roomie you pray you don't get.\r\nYou know what I'm saying?\r\n\r\n1246\r\n01:30:33,010 --> 01:30:35,762\r\nSix-to-twelve, armed burglary.\r\n\r\n1247\r\n01:30:36,013 --> 01:30:38,306\r\nSaid he pulled hundreds ofjobs.\r\n\r\n1248\r\n01:30:38,516 --> 01:30:4