78 --> 01:41:42,929\r\n...but I drove her away.\r\n\r\n1394\r\n01:41:44,431 --> 01:41:47,141\r\nThat's why she died, because of me...\r\n\r\n1395\r\n01:41:47,309 --> 01:41:48,684\r\n...the way I am.\r\n\r\n1396\r\n01:41:57,694 --> 01:41:59,529\r\nThat don't make you a murderer.\r\n\r\n1397\r\n01:42:02,908 --> 01:42:04,700\r\nBad husband, maybe.\r\n\r\n1398\r\n01:42:08,330 --> 01:42:11,582\r\nFeel bad about it if you want,\r\nbut you didn't pull the trigger.\r\n\r\n1399\r\n01:42:11,792 --> 01:42:13,126\r\nNo, I didn't.\r\n\r\n1400\r\n01:42:13,544 --> 01:42:15,461\r\nSomebody else did.\r\n\r\n1401\r\n01:42:16,713 --> 01:42:18,798\r\nAnd I wound up in here.\r\n\r\n1402\r\n01:42:21,260 --> 01:42:22,885\r\nBad luck, I guess.\r\n\r\n1403\r\n01:42:25,764 --> 01:42:29,517\r\n- Yeah.\r\n- It floats around.\r\n\r\n1404\r\n01:42:30,561 --> 01:42:32,770\r\nIt's got to land on somebody.\r\n\r\n1405\r\n01:42:33,689 --> 01:42:35,565\r\nIt was my turn, that's all.\r\n\r\n1406\r\n01:42:36,275 --> 01:42:39,068\r\nI was in the path of the tornado.\r\n\r\n1407\r\n01:42:44,992 --> 01:42:48,953\r\nI just didn't expect the storm\r\nwould last as long as it has.\r\n\r\n1408\r\n01:42:53,292 --> 01:42:55,001\r\nThink you'll ever get out of here?\r\n\r\n1409\r\n01:42:56,253 --> 01:42:57,670\r\nMe?\r\n\r\n1410\r\n01:43:00,257 --> 01:43:01,591\r\nYeah.\r\n\r\n1411\r\n01:43:02,593 --> 01:43:04,886\r\nOne day, when I got\r\na long, white beard...\r\n\r\n1412\r\n01:43:05,095 --> 01:43:09,182\r\n...and two or three marbles rolling\r\naround upstairs, they'll let me out.\r\n\r\n1413\r\n01:43:10,267 --> 01:43:11,934\r\nI tell you where I'd go.\r\n\r\n1414\r\n01:43:13,395 --> 01:43:15,104\r\nZihuatanejo.\r\n\r\n1415\r\n01:43:15,939 --> 01:43:17,106\r\nSay what?\r\n\r\n1416\r\n01:43:17,441 --> 01:43:19,275\r\nZihuatanejo.\r\n\r\n1417\r\n01:43:20,194 --> 01:43:21,861\r\nIt's in Mexico.\r\n\r\n1418\r\n01:43:23,238 --> 01:43:25,364\r\nA little place on the Pacific Ocean.\r\n\r\n1419\r\n01:43:26,491 --> 01:43:29,285\r\nYou know what the Mexicans say\r\nabout the Pacific?\r\n\r\n1420\r\n01:43:29,453 --> 01:43:33,122\r\n- No.\r\n- They say it has no memory.\r\n\r\n1421\r\n01:43:35,083 --> 01:43:37,752\r\nThat's where I want to live\r\nthe rest of my life.\r\n\r\n1422\r\n01:43:39,379 --> 01:43:41,881\r\nA warm place with no memory.\r\n\r\n1423\r\n01:43:45,135 --> 01:43:47,053\r\nOpen up a little hotel...\r\n\r\n1424\r\n01:43:48,764 --> 01:43:50,264\r\n...right on the beach.\r\n\r\n1425\r\n01:43:50,849 --> 01:43:53,059\r\nBuy some worthless old boat...\r\n\r\n1426\r\n01:43:53,602 --> 01:43:55,228\r\n...and fix it up new.\r\n\r\n1427\r\n01:43:57,981 --> 01:43:59,190\r\nTake my guests out...\r\n\r\n1428\r\n01:44:00,025 --> 01:44:01,400\r\n...charter fishing.\r\n\r\n1429\r\n01:44:05,239 --> 01:44:06,989\r\nZihuatanejo.\r\n\r\n1430\r\n01:44:10,494 --> 01:44:14,372\r\nIn a place like that, I could use\r\na man that knows how to get things.\r\n\r\n1431\r\n01:44:20,921 --> 01:44:23,756\r\nI don't think I could make it\r\non the outside, Andy.\r\n\r\n1432\r\n01:44:30,430 --> 01:44:32,515\r\nI been in here most of my life.\r\n\r\n1433\r\n01:44:33,934 --> 01:44:35,685\r\nI'm an institutional man now.\r\n\r\n1434\r\n01:44:36,603 --> 01:44:38,354\r\nJust like Brooks was.\r\n\r\n1435\r\n01:44:38,981 --> 01:44:41,524\r\nWell, you underestimate yourself.\r\n\r\n1436\r\n01:44:42,067 --> 01:44:43,693\r\nI don't think so.\r\n\r\n1437\r\n01:44:47,531 --> 01:44:51,450\r\nIn here I'm the guy who can get things\r\nfor you, sure, but...\r\n\r\n1438\r\n01:44:52,202 --> 01:44:54,745\r\n...outside all you need\r\nis the Yellow Pages.\r\n\r\n1439\r\n01:44:54,955 --> 01:44:57,206\r\nHell, I wouldn't know\r\nwhere to begin.\r\n\r\n1440\r\n01:44:59,334 --> 01:45:00,960\r\nPacific Ocean?\r\n\r\n1441\r\n01:45:01,378 --> 01:45:02,586\r\nShit.\r\n\r\n1442\r\n01:45:02,963 --> 01:45:05,172\r\nScare me to death, something that big.\r\n\r\n1443\r\n01:45:05,382 --> 01:45:06,674\r\nNot me.\r\n\r\n1444\r\n01:45:07,884 --> 01:45:10,636\r\nI didn't shoot my wife,\r\nand I didn't shoot her lover.\r\n\r\n1445\r\n01:45:12,389 --> 01:45:15,599\r\nWhatever mistakes I made,\r\nI've paid for them and then some.\r\n\r\n1446\r\n01:45:16,643 --> 01:45:18,144\r\nThat hotel, that boat...\r\n\r\n1447\r\n01:45:19,896 --> 01:45:22,148\r\nI don't think that's too much to ask.\r\n\r\n1448\r\n01:45:27,070 --> 01:45:29,488\r\nYou shouldn't be doing this to yourself.\r\n\r\n1449\r\n01:45:29,698 --> 01:45:31,741\r\nThis is just shitty pipe dreams.\r\n\r\n1450\r\n01:45:32,159 --> 01:45:34,618\r\nMexico is way down there\r\nand you're in here...\r\n\r\n1451\r\n01:45:34,828 --> 01:45:36,412\r\n...and that's the way it is.\r\n\r\n1452\r\n01:45:36,747 --> 01:45:39,582\r\nYeah, right. That's the way it is.\r\n\r\n1453\r\n01:45:41,084 --> 01:45:43,461\r\nIt's down there and I'm in here.\r\n\r\n1454\r\n01:45:46,048 --> 01:45:48,758\r\nI guess it comes down\r\nto a simple choice.\r\n\r\n1455\r\n01:45:51,678 --> 01:45:53,179\r\nGet busy living...\r\n\r\n1456\r\n01:45:54,556 --> 01:45:56,599\r\n...or get busy dying.\r\n\r\n1457\r\n01:46:00,228 --> 01:46:01,937\r\nRED:\r\nAndy.\r\n\r\n1458\r\n01:46:05,025 --> 01:46:06,692\r\nANDY:\r\nRed?\r\n\r\n1459\r\n01:46:08,695 --> 01:46:11,447\r\nIf you ever get out of here,\r\ndo me a favor.\r\n\r\n1460\r\n01:46:11,615 --> 01:46:13,908\r\nSure, Andy. Anything.\r\n\r\n1461\r\n01:46:15,786 --> 01:46:19,622\r\nThere's a big hayfield up near Buxton.\r\nYou know where Buxton is?\r\n\r\n1462\r\n01:46:21,124 --> 01:46:24,251\r\n- A lot of hayfields up there.\r\n- One in particular.\r\n\r\n1463\r\n01:46:24,461 --> 01:46:28,381\r\nIt's got a long rock wall\r\nwith a big oak tree at the north end.\r\n\r\n1464\r\n01:46:28,590 --> 01:46:31,467\r\nIt's like something\r\nout of a Robert Frost poem.\r\n\r\n1465\r\n01:46:32,386 --> 01:46:34,887\r\nIt's where I asked my wife to marry me.\r\n\r\n1466\r\n01:46:36,306 --> 01:46:38,391\r\nWe went there for a picnic...\r\n\r\n1467\r\n01:46:38,809 --> 01:46:40,893\r\n...and made love under that oak...\r\n\r\n1468\r\n01:46:41,561 --> 01:46:43,813\r\n...and I asked and she said yes.\r\n\r\n1469\r\n01:46:47,818 --> 01:46:49,652\r\nPromise me, Red.\r\n\r\n1470\r\n01:46:50,487 --> 01:46:52,113\r\nIf you ever get out...\r\n\r\n1471\r\n01:46:52,322 --> 01:46:53,823\r\n...find that spot.\r\n\r\n1472\r\n01:46:54,991 --> 01:46:59,829\r\nAt the base of that wall, there's a rock\r\nthat has no earthly business in Maine.\r\n\r\n1473\r\n01:47:00,956 --> 01:47:03,999\r\nPiece of black, volcanic glass.\r\n\r\n1474\r\n01:47:06,670 --> 01:47:09,338\r\nSomething's buried under it\r\nI want you to have.\r\n\r\n1475\r\n01:47:10,090 --> 01:47:11,340\r\nWhat, Andy?\r\n\r\n1476\r\n01:47:11,758 --> 01:47:13,509\r\nWhat's buried under there?\r\n\r\n1477\r\n01:47:15,095 --> 01:47:16,971\r\nYou'll have to pry it up...\r\n\r\n1478\r\n01:47:17,180 --> 01:47:18,431\r\n...to see.\r\n\r\n1479\r\n01:47:24,438 --> 01:47:26,272\r\nNo, I'm telling you. The guy is...\r\n\r\n1480\r\n01:47:26,940 --> 01:47:28,691\r\nHe's talking funny.\r\n\r\n1481\r\n01:47:29,776 --> 01:47:31,485\r\nI'm really worried about him.\r\n\r\n1482\r\n01:47:31,862 --> 01:47:33,320\r\nLet's keep an eye on him.\r\n\r\n1483\r\n01:47:33,530 --> 01:47:36,782\r\nThat's fine during the day,\r\nbut at night he's all alone.\r\n\r\n1484\r\n01:47:38,201 --> 01:47:39,368\r\nOh, Lord.\r\n\r\n1485\r\n01:47:40,704 --> 01:47:42,288\r\nWhat?\r\n\r\n1486\r\n01:47:43,039 --> 01:47:45,791\r\nAndy come down\r\nto the loading dock today.\r\n\r\n1487\r\n01:47:46,001 --> 01:47:48,085\r\nHe asked me for a length of rope.\r\n\r\n1488\r\n01:47:48,295 --> 01:47:51,005\r\n- Rope?\r\n- Six feet long.\r\n\r\n1489\r\n01:47:51,214 --> 01:47:52,590\r\nAnd you gave it to him.\r\n\r\n1490\r\n01:47:53,467 --> 01:47:55,259\r\nSure I did. Why wouldn't I?\r\n\r\n1491\r\n01:47:55,469 --> 01:47:57,052\r\nJesus! Heywood.\r\n\r\n1492\r\n01:47:57,637 --> 01:47:59,597\r\nHow was I supposed to know?\r\n\r\n1493\r\n01:47:59,806 --> 01:48:01,390\r\nRemember Brooks Hatlen?\r\n\r\n1494\r\n01:48:01,600 --> 01:48:05,311\r\nNo. Andy would never do that.\r\n\r\n1495\r\n01:48:05,896 --> 01:48:07,354\r\nNever.\r\n\r\n1496\r\n01:48:09,065 --> 01:48:10,399\r\nI don't know.\r\n\r\n1497\r\n01:48:13,236 --> 01:48:15,237\r\nEvery man has his breaking point.\r\n\r\n1498\r\n01:48:17,574 --> 01:48:19,867\r\nLickety-split. Want to get home.\r\n\r\n1499\r\n01:48:20,160 --> 01:48:21,911\r\nJust about finished, sir.\r\n\r\n1500\r\n01:48:39,054 --> 01:48:40,679\r\nThree deposits tonight.\r\n\r\n1501\r\n01:48:48,647 --> 01:48:50,564\r\nGet my stuff down to the laundry.\r\n\r\n1502\r\n01:48:50,774 --> 01:48:52,399\r\nAnd shine my shoes.\r\n\r\n1503\r\n01:48:52,609 --> 01:48:55,528\r\n- I want them looking like mirrors.\r\n- Yes, sir.\r\n\r\n1504\r\n01:49:01,034 --> 01:49:02,493\r\nIt's good having you back, Andy.\r\n\r\n1505\r\n01:49:03,453 --> 01:49:05,287\r\nPlace wasn't the same without you.\r\n\r\n1506\r\n01:49:07,624 --> 01:49:10,459\r\n[NORTON WHISTLING]\r\n\r\n1507\r\n01:49:52,168 --> 01:49:53,544\r\nGUARD:\r\nLights out!\r\n\r\n1508\r\n01:50:26,077 --> 01:50:28,621\r\nRED:\r\nI've had some long nights in the stir.\r\n\r\n1509\r\n01:50:29,164 --> 01:50:31,832\r\nAlone in the dark\r\nwith nothing but your thoughts...\r\n\r\n1510\r\n01:50:32,042 --> 01:50:34,710\r\n...time can draw out like a blade.\r\n\r\n1511\r\n01:50:40,050 --> 01:50:43,052\r\nThat was the longest night of my life.\r\n\r\n1512\r\n01:50:52,562 --> 01:50:55,105\r\n[HORN BUZZING]\r\n\r\n1513\r\n01:50:58,902 --> 01:51:00,069\r\nGUARD 1:\r\nGive me a count!\r\n\r\n1514\r\n01:51:04,574 --> 01:51:07,409\r\nGUARD 2:\r\nTier 3 south, clear!\r\n\r\n1515\r\n01:51:10,538 --> 01:51:13,707\r\nMan missing on tier 2, cell 245!\r\n\r\n1516\r\n01:51:13,917 --> 01:51:14,958\r\nDufresne!\r\n\r\n1517\r\n01:51:15,502 --> 01:51:17,920\r\nCome out. You're holding up the show!\r\n\r\n1518\r\n01:51:21,091 --> 01:51:24,468\r\nDon't make me come down\r\nor I'll thump your skull for you!\r\n\r\n1519\r\n01:51:32,060 --> 01:51:35,896\r\nDamn it, you're putting me behind!\r\nI got a schedule to keep.\r\n\r\n1520\r\n01:51:36,106 --> 01:51:39,400\r\nYou'd better be sick or dead in there.\r\nI shit you not!\r\n\r\n1521\r\n01:51:39,609 --> 01:51:40,943\r\nYou hear me?\r\n\r\n1522\r\n01:51:47,033 --> 01:51:49,118\r\nOh, my Holy God.\r\n\r\n1523\r\n01:52:01,256 --> 01:52:04,299\r\n[SIREN WAILING]\r\n\r\n1524\r\n01:52:06,136 --> 01:52:08,679\r\nI want every man\r\non this cellblock questioned.\r\n\r\n1525\r\n01:52:09,139 --> 01:52:11,682\r\n- Start with that friend of his.\r\n- Who?\r\n\r\n1526\r\n01:52:11,850 --> 01:52:13,267\r\nHim.\r\n\r\n1527\r\n01:52:14,269 --> 01:52:15,811\r\nHADLEY:\r\nOpen 237.\r\n\r\n1528\r\n01:52:19,315 --> 01:52:22,985\r\nWhat do you mean, \"He just wasn't here\"?\r\nDon't say that to me.\r\n\r\n1529\r\n01:52:23,862 --> 01:52:26,447\r\n- Don't say that to me again.\r\n- But, sir, he wasn't.\r\n\r\n1530\r\n01:52:26,656 --> 01:52:30,159\r\nI can see that, Haig! Think I'm blind?\r\n\r\n1531\r\n01:52:30,827 --> 01:52:32,411\r\nIs that what you're saying?\r\n\r\n1532\r\n01:52:32,579 --> 01:52:35,080\r\n- Am I blind, Haig?\r\n- No, sir!\r\n\r\n1533\r\n01:52:35,999 --> 01:52:38,500\r\nWhat about you. You blind?\r\n\r\n1534\r\n01:52:39,002 --> 01:52:41,336\r\n- Tell me what this is.\r\n- Last night's count.\r\n\r\n1535\r\n01:52:41,504 --> 01:52:45,048\r\nUh-huh. You see Dufresne's name there?\r\nI sure do. Right there.\r\n\r\n1536\r\n01:52:45,258 --> 01:52:46,592\r\n\"Dufresne.\"\r\n\r\n1537\r\n01:52:48,261 --> 01:52:51,013\r\nHe was in his cell at lights out.\r\n\r\n1538\r\n01:52:51,181 --> 01:52:54,099\r\nStands to reason he'd still be here\r\nin the morning.\r\n\r\n1539\r\n01:52:54,434 --> 01:52:56,059\r\nI want him found.\r\n\r\n1540\r\n01:52:56,269 --> 01:52:59,730\r\nNot tomorrow, not after breakfast. Now!\r\n\r\n1541\r\n01:52:59,981 --> 01:53:01,190\r\nYes, sir.\r\n\r\n1542\r\n01:53:02,192 --> 01:53:05,986\r\nLet's go. Move your butts. Move it!\r\n\r\n1543\r\n01:53:07,864 --> 01:53:08,864\r\nStand.\r\n\r\n1544\r\n01:53:10,283 --> 01:53:11,700\r\nWell?\r\n\r\n1545\r\n01:53:14,788 --> 01:53:15,829\r\nWell, what?\r\n\r\n1546\r\n01:53:15,997 --> 01:53:19,458\r\nI see you two all the time.\r\nYou're thick as thieves, you are.\r\n\r\n1547\r\n01:53:20,543 --> 01:53:22,044\r\nHe must have said something.\r\n\r\n1548\r\n01:53:22,754 --> 01:53:25,672\r\nNo, sir, warden. Not a word.\r\n\r\n1549\r\n01:53:27,467 --> 01:53:30,052\r\nLord, it's a miracle!\r\n\r\n1550\r\n01:53:30,637 --> 01:53:33,222\r\nMan vanished like a fart in the wind.\r\n\r\n1551\r\n01:53:33,890 --> 01:53:35,057\r\nNothing left...\r\n\r\n1552\r\n01:53:35,892 --> 01:53:38,602\r\n...but some damn rocks\r\non a windowsill.\r\n\r\n1553\r\n01:53:38,812 --> 01:53:41,563\r\nAnd that cupcake on the wall.\r\nLet's ask her.\r\n\r\n1554\r\n01:53:41,731 --> 01:53:43,065\r\nMaybe she knows.\r\n\r\n1555\r\n01:53:43,233 --> 01:53:46,443\r\nWhat say there, fuzzy-britches?\r\nFeel like talking?\r\n\r\n1556\r\n01:53:46,778 --> 01:53:49,238\r\nOh, guess not.\r\n\r\n1557\r\n01:53:49,781 --> 01:53:51,990\r\nWhy should she be any different?\r\n\r\n1558\r\n01:53:53,076 --> 01:53:54,743\r\nThis is a conspiracy.\r\n\r\n1559\r\n01:53:55,370 --> 01:53:57,079\r\nThat's what this is.\r\n\r\n1560\r\n01:53:57,789 --> 01:54:01,542\r\nOne big, damn conspiracy!\r\n\r\n1561\r\n01:54:01,793 --> 01:54:03,794\r\nAnd everyone's in on it!\r\n\r\n1562\r\n01:54:04,420 --> 01:54:05,587\r\nIncluding her!\r\n\r\n1563\r\n01:54:40,623 --> 01:54:42,332\r\nRED:\r\nIn 1966...\r\n\r\n1564\r\n01:54:42,542 --> 01:54:44,960\r\n...Andy Dufresne escaped...\r\n\r\n1565\r\n01:54:45,128 --> 01:54:46,712\r\n...from Shawshank Prison.\r\n\r\n1566\r\n01:54:48,965 --> 01:54:51,508\r\nAll they found of him\r\nwas a muddy set of prison clothes...\r\n\r\n1567\r\n01:54:52,135 --> 01:54:53,677\r\n...a bar of soap...\r\n\r\n1568\r\n01:54:53,887 --> 01:54:55,470\r\n...and an old rock hammer...\r\n\r\n1569\r\n01:54:55,638 --> 01:54:58,140\r\n...damn near worn down to the nub.\r\n\r\n1570\r\n01:55:02,645 --> 01:55:07,399\r\nI remember thinking it would take a man\r\n600 years to tunnel through the wall with it.\r\n\r\n1571\r\n01:55:08,026 --> 01:55:10,652\r\nOld Andy did it in less than 20.\r\n\r\n1572\r\n01:55:28,963 --> 01:55:31,256\r\nOh, Andy loved geology.\r\n\r\n1573\r\n01:55:32,008 --> 01:55:35,177\r\nI imagine it appealed to\r\nhis meticulous nature.\r\n\r\n1574\r\n01:55:35,595 --> 01:55:37,429\r\nAn ice age here...\r\n\r\n1575\r\n01:55:37,847 --> 01:55:40,349\r\n...million years\r\nof mountain-building there.\r\n\r\n1576\r\n01:55:41,351 --> 01:55:44,186\r\nGeology is the study\r\nof pressure and time.\r\n\r\n1577\r\n01:55:45,021 --> 01:55:47,022\r\nThat's all it takes, really.\r\n\r\n1578\r\n01:55:47,774 --> 01:55:49,066\r\nPressure...\r\n\r\n1579\r\n01:55:49,525 --> 01:55:51,026\r\n...and time.\r\n\r\n1580\r\n01:55:52,111 --> 01:55:54,196\r\nThat and a big goddamn poster.\r\n\r\n1581\r\n01:55:55,657 --> 01:55:57,824\r\n[MAN COUGHING]\r\n\r\n1582\r\n01:55:57,992 --> 01:55:59,159\r\nLike I said...\r\n\r\n1583\r\n01:55:59,661 --> 01:56:03,664\r\n...in prison, a man will do anything\r\nto keep his mind occupied.\r\n\r\n1584\r\n01:56:06,459 --> 01:56:11,254\r\nSeems Andy's favorite hobby was toting\r\nhis wall out into the exercise yard...\r\n\r\n1585\r\n01:56:11,798 --> 01:56:13,715\r\n...a handful at a time.\r\n\r\n1586\r\n01:56:15,051 --> 01:56:17,094\r\nI guess after Tommy was killed...\r\n\r\n1587\r\n01:56:17,303 --> 01:56:20,263\r\n...Andy decided\r\nhe'd been here just about long enough.\r\n\r\n1588\r\n01:56:20,473 --> 01:56:23,058\r\nLickety-split. Want to get home.\r\n\r\n1589\r\n01:56:23,768 --> 01:56:25,811\r\nI'm just about finished, sir.\r\n\r\n1590\r\n01:56:47,250 --> 01:56:49,209\r\nThree deposits tonight.\r\n\r\n1591\r\n01:56:56,509 --> 01:56:58,802\r\nRED:\r\nAndy did like he was told.\r\n\r\n1592\r\n01:56:59,012 --> 01:57:02,514\r\nBuffed those shoes\r\nto a high mirror-shine.\r\n\r\n1593\r\n01:57:06,185 --> 01:57:08,478\r\nThe guards simply didn't notice.\r\n\r\n1594\r\n01:57:08,771 --> 01:57:10,272\r\nNeither did I.\r\n\r\n1595\r\n01:57:10,440 --> 01:57:11,982\r\nI mean, seriously...\r\n\r\n1596\r\n01:57:12,191 --> 01:57:15,193\r\n...how often do you really look\r\nat a man's shoes?\r\n\r\n1597\r\n01:59:18,734 --> 01:59:21,903\r\nAndy crawled to freedom\r\nthrough 500 yards...\r\n\r\n1598\r\n01:59:22,155 --> 01:59:25,490\r\n...of shit-smelling foulness\r\nI can't even imagine.\r\n\r\n1599\r\n01:59:26,492 --> 01:59:28,827\r\nOr maybe I just don't want to.\r\n\r\n1600\r\n01:59:33,249 --> 01:59:35,584\r\nFive hundred yards.\r\n\r\n1601\r\n01:59:36,085 --> 01:59:39,171\r\nThat's the length\r\nof five football fields.\r\n\r\n1602\r\n01:59:39,797 --> 01:59:42,382\r\nJust shy of half a mile.\r\n\r\n1603\r\n02:00:31,891 --> 02:00:34,809\r\n[LAUGHING]\r\n\r\n1604\r\n02:00:37,605 --> 02:00:42,192\r\nThe next morning, right about the time\r\nRaquel was spilling her little secret...\r\n\r\n1605\r\n02:00:42,485 --> 02:00:45,320\r\n...a man nobody ever\r\nlaid eyes on before...\r\n\r\n1606\r\n02:00:45,571 --> 02:00:48,156\r\n...strolled into\r\nthe Maine National Bank.\r\n\r\n1607\r\n02:00:48,741 --> 02:00:51,910\r\nUntil that moment, he didn't exist.\r\n\r\n1608\r\n02:00:52,495 --> 02:00:54,829\r\n- Except on paper.\r\n- May I help you?\r\n\r\n1609\r\n02:00:55,248 --> 02:00:57,165\r\nHe had all the proper ID...\r\n\r\n1610\r\n02:00:57,375 --> 02:01:01,086\r\nDriver's license, birth certificate,\r\nSocial Security card.\r\n\r\n1611\r\n02:01:01,504 --> 02:01:04,047\r\n- And the signature\r\nwas a spot-on match.\r\n\r\n1612\r\n02:01:04,257 --> 02:01:07,342\r\nI must say I'm sorry\r\nto be losing your business.\r\n\r\n1613\r\n02:01:07,551 --> 02:01:09,302\r\nI hope you'll enjoy living abroad.\r\n\r\n1614\r\n02:01:10,096 --> 02:01:11,680\r\nThank you.\r\n\r\n1615\r\n02:01:11,847 --> 02:01:13,014\r\nI'm sure I will.\r\n\r\n1616\r\n02:01:13,933 --> 02:01:17,269\r\nHere's your cashier's check, sir.\r\nWill there be anything else?\r\n\r\n1617\r\n02:01:17,478 --> 02:01:18,478\r\nPlease.\r\n\r\n1618\r\n02:01:19,021 --> 02:01:21,523\r\nWould you add this\r\nto your outgoing mail?\r\n\r\n1619\r\n02:01:22,024 --> 02:01:23,566\r\nI'd be happy to.\r\n\r\n1620\r\n02:01:25,027 --> 02:01:26,361\r\nGood day, sir.\r\n\r\n1621\r\n02:01:27,321 --> 02:01:31,741\r\nRED: Mr. Stevens visited nearly\r\na dozen banks in the Portland area.\r\n\r\n1622\r\n02:01:32,201 --> 02:01:33,827\r\nAll told, he blew town...\r\n\r\n1623\r\n02:01:34,036 --> 02:01:38,873\r\n...with better than $370,000\r\nof Warden Norton's money.\r\n\r\n1624\r\n02:01:39,542 --> 02:01:42,335\r\nSeverance pay for 19 years.\r\n\r\n1625\r\n02:01:42,503 --> 02:01:44,045\r\n[PHONE RINGING]\r\n\r\n1626\r\n02:01:49,552 --> 02:01:51,761\r\nWOMAN:\r\nGood morning, Portland Daily Bugle.\r\n\r\n1627\r\n02:01:58,394 --> 02:02:00,895\r\n[SIREN WAILING]\r\n\r\n1628\r\n02:02:44,607 --> 02:02:47,567\r\nByron Hadley?\r\nYou have the right to remain silent.\r\n\r\n1629\r\n02:02:47,818 --> 02:02:52,280\r\nIf you give up this right, anything you\r\nsay can be held against you in court.\r\n\r\n1630\r\n02:02:52,698 --> 02:02:57,160\r\nRED: I wasn't there to see it, but I hear\r\nByron Hadley sobbed like a little girl...\r\n\r\n1631\r\n02:02:57,370 --> 02:02:58,870\r\n...when they took him away.\r\n\r\n1632\r\n02:03:04,752 --> 02:03:08,129\r\nNorton had no intention\r\nof going that quietly.\r\n\r\n1633\r\n02:03:24,105 --> 02:03:25,480\r\nSamuel Norton.\r\n\r\n1634\r\n02:03:25,648 --> 02:03:27,649\r\nWe have a warrant for your arrest.\r\nOpen up.\r\n\r\n1635\r\n02:03:27,817 --> 02:03:29,567\r\n[KNOCKING]\r\n\r\n1636\r\n02:03:31,278 --> 02:03:34,280\r\nNorton. Open the door.\r\n\r\n1637\r\n02:03:34,448 --> 02:03:35,698\r\nI'm not sure which key.\r\n\r\n1638\r\n02:03:38,494 --> 02:03:40,412\r\nNorton!\r\n\r\n1639\r\n02:03:45,835 --> 02:03:47,794\r\nMake it easy on yourself, Norton!\r\n\r\n1640\r\n02:03:59,306 --> 02:04:02,767\r\nRED: I like to think the last thing\r\nthat went through his head...\r\n\r\n1641\r\n02:04:02,977 --> 02:04:04,561\r\n...other than that bullet...\r\n\r\n1642\r\n02:04:04,770 --> 02:04:09,190\r\n...was to wonder how the hell\r\nAndy Dufresne ever got the best of him.\r\n\r\n1643\r\n02:04:11,694 --> 02:04:15,196\r\nNot long after the warden\r\ndeprived us of his company...\r\n\r\n1644\r\n02:04:15,448 --> 02:04:17,532\r\n...I got a postcard in the mail.\r\n\r\n1645\r\n02:04:18,993 --> 02:04:21,828\r\nIt was blank, but the postmark said...\r\n\r\n1646\r\n02:04:22,037 --> 02:04:24,164\r\n...Fort Hancock, Texas.\r\n\r\n1647\r\n02:04:24,707 --> 02:04:26,040\r\nFort Hancock...\r\n\r\n1648\r\n02:04:26,333 --> 02:04:28,042\r\n...right on the border.\r\n\r\n1649\r\n02:04:28,461 --> 02:04:30,462\r\nThat's where Andy crossed.\r\n\r\n1650\r\n02:04:31,046 --> 02:04:35,175\r\nWhen I picture him heading south\r\nin his own car with the top down...\r\n\r\n1651\r\n02:04:35,509 --> 02:04:37,719\r\n...it always makes me laugh.\r\n\r\n1652\r\n02:04:39,555 --> 02:04:41,139\r\nAndy Dufresne...\r\n\r\n1653\r\n02:04:41,515 --> 02:04:43,558\r\n...who crawled through\r\na river of shit...\r\n\r\n1654\r\n02:04:43,726 --> 02:04:46,144\r\n...and came out clean\r\non the other side.\r\n\r\n1655\r\n02:04:46,979 --> 02:04:48,354\r\nAndy Dufresne...\r\n\r\n1656\r\n02:04:49,148 --> 02:04:50,732\r\n...headed for the Pacific.\r\n\r\n1657\r\n02:04:53,736 --> 02:04:55,904\r\nHadley's got him\r\nby the throat, right?\r\n\r\n1658\r\n02:04:56,071 --> 02:04:59,908\r\nHe says, \"I believe this boy's\r\nabout to have himself an accident.\"\r\n\r\n1659\r\n02:05:00,075 --> 02:05:02,952\r\nRED: Those of us who knew him best\r\ntalk about him often.\r\n\r\n1660\r\n02:05:03,621 --> 02:05:05,330\r\nI swear, the stuff he pulled...\r\n\r\n1661\r\n02:05:05,539 --> 02:05:08,500\r\n\"My friends could use\r\na couple of beers.\"\r\n\r\n1662\r\n02:05:08,834 --> 02:05:10,502\r\nAnd he got it!\r\n\r\n1663\r\n02:05:11,754 --> 02:05:14,130\r\nRED:\r\nSometimes it makes me sad, though...\r\n\r\n1664\r\n02:05:14,423 --> 02:05:15,840\r\n...Andy being gone.\r\n\r\n1665\r\n02:05:16,550 --> 02:05:20,678\r\nI have to remind myself that\r\nsome birds aren't meant to be caged.\r\n\r\n1666\r\n02:05:21,138 --> 02:05:23,223\r\nTheir feathers are just too bright.\r\n\r\n1667\r\n02:05:24,934 --> 02:05:26,643\r\nAnd when they fly away...\r\n\r\n1668\r\n02:05:27,102 --> 02:05:31,481\r\n...the part of you that knows it was\r\na sin to lock them up does rejoice.\r\n\r\n1669\r\n02:05:32,566 --> 02:05:33,816\r\nBut still...\r\n\r\n1670\r\n02:05:34,276 --> 02:05:38,613\r\n...the place you live in is that much\r\nmore drab and empty that they're gone.\r\n\r\n1671\r\n02:05:42,826 --> 02:05:45,203\r\nI guess I just miss my friend.\r\n\r\n1672\r\n02:06:09,645 --> 02:06:10,812\r\nPlease sit down.\r\n\r\n1673\r\n02:06:16,652 --> 02:06:18,236\r\nEllis Boyd Redding...\r\n\r\n1674\r\n02:06:18,779 --> 02:06:22,031\r\n...your files say you've served\r\n40 years of a life sentence.\r\n\r\n1675\r\n02:06:22,825 --> 02:06:24,993\r\nYou feel you've been rehabilitated?\r\n\r\n1676\r\n02:06:26,829 --> 02:06:28,413\r\nRehabilitated?\r\n\r\n1677\r\n02:06:30,457 --> 02:06:32,333\r\nWell, now, let me see.\r\n\r\n1678\r\n02:06:33,335 --> 02:06:35,670\r\nI don't have any idea what that means.\r\n\r\n1679\r\n02:06:37,798 --> 02:06:40,049\r\nIt means you're ready\r\nto rejoin society...\r\n\r\n1680\r\n02:06:40,634 --> 02:06:42,969\r\nI know what you think it means, sonny.\r\n\r\n1681\r\n02:06:45,139 --> 02:06:47,140\r\nTo me it's just a made-up word.\r\n\r\n1682\r\n02:06:48,475 --> 02:06:50,810\r\nA politician's word so that...\r\n\r\n1683\r\n02:06:51,228 --> 02:06:54,772\r\n...young fellas like yourself\r\ncan wear a suit and a tie...\r\n\r\n1684\r\n02:06:55,232 --> 02:06:56,858\r\n...and have a job.\r\n\r\n1685\r\n02:06:58,819 --> 02:07:00,903\r\nWhat do you really want to know?\r\n\r\n1686\r\n02:07:01,697 --> 02:07:03,656\r\nAm I sorry for what I did?\r\n\r\n1687\r\n02:07:04,074 --> 02:07:05,366\r\nWell, are you?\r\n\r\n1688\r\n02:07:07,161 --> 02:07:09,996\r\nThere's not a day goes by\r\nI don't feel regret.\r\n\r\n1689\r\n02:07:11,373 --> 02:07:14,834\r\nNot because I'm in here\r\nor because you think I should.\r\n\r\n1690\r\n02:07:18,297 --> 02:07:20,882\r\nI look back on the way I was then...\r\n\r\n1691\r\n02:07:23,010 --> 02:07:24,344\r\n...a young...\r\n\r\n1692\r\n02:07:25,262 --> 02:07:28,765\r\n...stupid kid who committed\r\nthat terrible crime.\r\n\r\n1693\r\n02:07:31,769 --> 02:07:33,478\r\nI want to talk to him.\r\n\r\n1694\r\n02:07:35,397 --> 02:07:37,899\r\nI want to try\r\nand talk some sense to him.\r\n\r\n1695\r\n02:07:38,609 --> 02:07:40,568\r\nTell him the way things are.\r\n\r\n1696\r\n02:07:42,655 --> 02:07:44,072\r\nBut I can't.\r\n\r\n1697\r\n02:07:46,283 --> 02:07:48,284\r\nThat kid's long gone...\r\n\r\n1698\r\n02:07:49,495 --> 02:07:52,246\r\n...and this old man is all that's left.\r\n\r\n1699\r\n02:07:53,666 --> 02:07:55,124\r\nI got to live with that.\r\n\r\n1700\r\n02:07:56,502 --> 02:07:58,211\r\nRehabilitated?\r\n\r\n1701\r\n02:07:58,587 --> 02:08:00,421\r\nIt's just a bullshit word.\r\n\r\n1702\r\n02:08:01,340 --> 02:08:06,094\r\nSo you go on and stamp your forms,\r\nsonny, and stop wasting my time.\r\n\r\n1703\r\n02:08:07,346 --> 02:08:09,597\r\nBecause to tell you the truth...\r\n\r\n1704\r\n02:08:09,932 --> 02:08:11,933\r\n...I don't give a shit.\r\n\r\n1705\r\n02:09:38,479 --> 02:09:39,854\r\nHere you go, miss.\r\n\r\n1706\r\n02:09:42,816 --> 02:09:43,858\r\nRestroom break, boss?\r\n\r\n1707\r\n02:09:49,656 --> 02:09:54,202\r\nYou don't need to ask me every time you\r\nneed to go take a piss. Just go. Understand?\r\n\r\n1708\r\n02:09:55,204 --> 02:09:56,829\r\nYes, sir.\r\n\r\n1709\r\n02:10:07,216 --> 02:10:10,301\r\nRED: Forty years I've been asking\r\npermission to piss.\r\n\r\n1710\r\n02:10:11,136 --> 02:10:14,138\r\nI can't squeeze a drop without say-so.\r\n\r\n1711\r\n02:10:17,643 --> 02:10:19,811\r\nThere's a harsh truth to face.\r\n\r\n1712\r\n02:10:21,480 --> 02:10:24,398\r\nNo way I'm going to make it\r\non the outside.\r\n\r\n1713\r\n02:10:32,241 --> 02:10:35,952\r\nAll I do anymore is think of ways\r\nto break my parole...\r\n\r\n1714\r\n02:10:36,745 --> 02:10:39,247\r\n...so maybe they'd send me back.\r\n\r\n1715\r\n02:10:44,419 --> 02:10:46,879\r\nTerrible thing, to live in fear.\r\n\r\n1716\r\n02:10:47,756 --> 02:10:49,423\r\nBrooks Hatlen knew it.\r\n\r\n1717\r\n02:10:49,633 --> 02:10:51,592\r\nKnew it all too well.\r\n\r\n1718\r\n02:10:53,178 --> 02:10:56,597\r\nAll I want is to be back\r\nwhere things make sense.\r\n\r\n1719\r\n02:10:57,015 --> 02:10:59,767\r\nWhere I won't have to be afraid\r\nall the time.\r\n\r\n1720\r\n02:11:01,770 --> 02:11:04,105\r\nOnly one thing stops me.\r\n\r\n1721\r\n02:11:05,566 --> 02:11:07,942\r\nA promise I made to Andy.\r\n\r\n1722\r\n02:11:28,463 --> 02:11:29,797\r\nMAN:\r\nThere it is.\r\n\r\n1723\r\n02:11:40,225 --> 02:11:41,893\r\nRED:\r\nMuch obliged, sir.\r\n\r\n1724\r\n02:15:21,196 --> 02:15:22,488\r\nANDY:\r\nDear Red:\r\n\r\n1725\r\n02:15:22,697 --> 02:15:25,199\r\nIf you're reading this,\r\nyou've gotten out...\r\n\r\n1726\r\n02:15:25,367 --> 02:15:29,537\r\n...and if you've come this far,\r\nmaybe you're willing to come a little further.\r\n\r\n1727\r\n02:15:29,704 --> 02:15:32,206\r\nYou remember the name\r\nof the town, don't you?\r\n\r\n1728\r\n02:15:34,501 --> 02:15:36,001\r\nZihuatanejo.\r\n\r\n1729\r\n02:15:37,629 --> 02:15:41,215\r\nANDY: I could use a good man\r\nto help me get my project on wheels.\r\n\r\n1730\r\n02:15:41,716 --> 02:15:45,261\r\nI'll keep an eye out for you,\r\nand the chessboard ready.\r\n\r\n1731\r\n02:15:46,054 --> 02:15:47,471\r\nRemember, Red...\r\n\r\n1732\r\n02:15:47,806 --> 02:15:49,890\r\n...hope is a good thing...\r\n\r\n1733\r\n02:15:50,100 --> 02:15:52,101\r\n...maybe the best of things.\r\n\r\n1734\r\n02:15:52,310 --> 02:15:54,478\r\nAnd no good thing ever dies.\r\n\r\n1735\r\n02:15:55,021 --> 02:15:57,898\r\nI will be hoping\r\nthat this letter finds you...\r\n\r\n1736\r\n02:15:58,066 --> 02:15:59,817\r\n...and finds you well.\r\n\r\n1737\r\n02:16:00,318 --> 02:16:01,569\r\nYour friend...\r\n\r\n1738\r\n02:16:01,736 --> 02:16:02,903\r\n...Andy.\r\n\r\n1739\r\n02:16:36,771 --> 02:16:38,480\r\nRED:\r\n\"Get busy living...\r\n\r\n1740\r\n02:16:38,690 --> 02:16:40,608\r\n...or get busy dying.\"\r\n\r\n1741\r\n02:16:43,278 --> 02:16:45,446\r\nThat's goddamn right.\r\n\r\n1742\r\n02:16:50,702 --> 02:16:52,828\r\nFor the second time in my life...\r\n\r\n1743\r\n02:16:53,079 --> 02:16:55,623\r\n...I'm guilty of committing a crime.\r\n\r\n1744\r\n02:16:56,708 --> 02:16:58,626\r\nParole violation.\r\n\r\n1745\r\n02:16:59,294 --> 02:17:02,963\r\nOf course, I doubt they'll toss up\r\nany roadblocks for that.\r\n\r\n1746\r\n02:17:03,632 --> 02:17:05,674\r\nNot for an old crook like me.\r\n\r\n1747\r\n02:17:05,884 --> 02:17:07,927\r\nFort Hancock, Texas, please.\r\n\r\n1748\r\n02:17:11,598 --> 02:17:16,310\r\nRED: I find I'm so excited I can barely\r\nsit still or hold a thought in my head.\r\n\r\n1749\r\n02:17:16,770 --> 02:17:20,105\r\nI think it's the excitement\r\nonly a free man can feel.\r\n\r\n1750\r\n02:17:20,315 --> 02:17:22,816\r\nA free man at the start\r\nof a long journey...\r\n\r\n1751\r\n02:17:22,984 --> 02:17:25,611\r\n...whose conclusion is uncertain.\r\n\r\n1752\r\n02:17:28,615 --> 02:17:31,283\r\nI hope I can make it across the border.\r\n\r\n1753\r\n02:17:32,786 --> 02:17:35,829\r\nI hope to see my friend\r\nand shake his hand.\r\n\r\n1754\r\n02:17:37,666 --> 02:17:41,752\r\nI hope the Pacific is as blue\r\nas it has been in my dreams.\r\n\r\n1755\r\n02:17:43,588 --> 02:17:44,797\r\nI hope.","markerStore":{"nextMarkerId":97,"markersById":{"0":{"range":{"start":{"row":0,"column":0},"end":{"row":0,"column":0}},"properties":{"type":"selection","editorId":8,"goalScreenRange":null},"reversed":false,"tailed":false,"valid":true,"invalidate":"never","maintainHistory":true}},"version":2},"history":{"version":3,"nextCheckpointId":1,"undoStack":[],"redoStack":[]},"encoding":"utf8","filePath":"/Users/joegesualdo/Downloads/the-shawshank-redemption-english-yify-36147/The Shawshank Redemption (1994) [1080p] x264 - Jalucian-eng.srt","digestWhenLastPersisted":"7abee3e79f3b1decd5a22866a10a1da0435ece7f","preferredLineEnding":null,"deserializer":"TextBuffer","version":2}],"deserializer":"Project"},"workspace":{"paneContainer":{"root":{"id":3,"items":[{"id":8,"softTabs":true,"displayBuffer":{"id":9,"softWrapped":false,"scrollTop":2899,"scrollLeft":0,"tokenizedBuffer":{"bufferPath":"/Users/joegesualdo/Downloads/the-shawshank-redemption-english-yify-36147/The Shawshank Redemption (1994) [1080p] x264 - Jalucian-eng.srt","largeFileMode":false,"deserializer":"TokenizedBuffer"},"largeFileMode":false,"deserializer":"DisplayBuffer"},"deserializer":"TextEditor"}],"activeItemURI":"/Users/joegesualdo/Downloads/the-shawshank-redemption-english-yify-36147/The Shawshank Redemption (1994) [1080p] x264 - Jalucian-eng.srt","focused":true,"flexScale":1,"deserializer":"Pane"},"activePaneId":3,"deserializer":"PaneContainer","version":1},"fullScreen":false,"packagesWithActiveGrammars":["language-hyperlink","language-todo"],"deserializer":"Workspace"},"packageStates":{"fuzzy-finder":{"/Users/joegesualdo/Downloads/the-shawshank-redemption-english-yify-36147/The Shawshank Redemption (1994) [1080p] x264 - Jalucian-eng.srt":1442887546183},"metrics":{"sessionLength":18898},"tabs":[{}],"tree-view":{"directoryExpansionStates":{"/Users/joegesualdo/Downloads/the-shawshank-redemption-english-yify-36147":{"isExpanded":true,"entries":{}}},"selectedPath":"/Users/joegesualdo/Downloads/the-shawshank-redemption-english-yify-36147/The Shawshank Redemption (1994) [1080p] x264 - Jalucian-e